Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.84,0:00:19.64,English1,,0,0,0,,As the sun dips below the horizon
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.84,0:00:22.64,English1,,0,0,0,,its light begins to fade.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.64,0:00:27.24,English1,,0,0,0,,Night falls and our world descends into darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.96,0:00:46.36,English1,,0,0,0,,Today, in our street-lit towns and cities,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.36,0:00:49.60,English1,,0,0,0,,we rarely experience true darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.60,0:00:52.24,English1,,0,0,0,,But without our eyes to guide us,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.24,0:00:55.84,English1,,0,0,0,,the world becomes a much more mysterious place.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.32,0:01:14.16,English1,,0,0,0,,I can't see anything now,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.16,0:01:17.64,English1,,0,0,0,,but strangely I can still sense the presence of the trees
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.64,0:01:19.24,English1,,0,0,0,,enveloping me in the gloom.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.96,0:01:24.36,English1,,0,0,0,,I can't see them, but I know there's something out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.60,0:01:35.84,English1,,0,0,0,,And in the same way, as we've explored the cosmos,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.84,0:01:38.20,English1,,0,0,0,,we've come to realise we can only see
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.20,0:01:40.60,English1,,0,0,0,,the merest hint of what's out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.20,0:01:48.00,English1,,0,0,0,,Our best estimate is that more than 99% of the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.00,0:01:52.72,English1,,0,0,0,,lies hidden in the dark, invisible to our telescopes
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.72,0:01:54.80,English1,,0,0,0,,and beyond our comprehension.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.28,0:02:00.84,English1,,0,0,0,,This film is the story of how we went from thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.84,0:02:04.40,English1,,0,0,0,,we were close to a complete understanding of the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.40,0:02:08.84,English1,,0,0,0,,to realising we'd seen almost none of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.84,0:02:12.92,English1,,0,0,0,,and the extraordinary quest to uncover what's really out there
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.92,0:02:14.32,English1,,0,0,0,,in the dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.92,0:02:21.80,English1,,0,0,0,,It's perhaps the most important undertaking in science,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.80,0:02:25.84,English1,,0,0,0,,because our universe was forged in darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.84,0:02:29.52,English1,,0,0,0,,And darkness will one day tear it apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.40,0:02:53.84,English1,,0,0,0,,For centuries, scientists have used light to build up a seemingly
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.84,0:02:56.56,English1,,0,0,0,,comprehensive picture of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.20,0:03:01.00,English1,,0,0,0,,We'd discovered that the Earth was just one planet
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.00,0:03:02.56,English1,,0,0,0,,in orbit around the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.88,0:03:06.48,English1,,0,0,0,,And that the sun was itself a star,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.48,0:03:09.52,English1,,0,0,0,,made of the same stuff as the billions upon billions
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.52,0:03:14.12,English1,,0,0,0,,of stars that light up a vast - perhaps endless - cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.08,0:03:29.56,English1,,0,0,0,,But there was one niggling problem that had remained unsolved
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.56,0:03:32.72,English1,,0,0,0,,for over 400 years, and it was this -
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.72,0:03:34.48,English1,,0,0,0,,with so many stars out there,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.48,0:03:36.48,English1,,0,0,0,,why was there any darkness at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.76,0:03:42.44,English1,,0,0,0,,The story of the dark begins with this simple question.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.00,0:03:47.60,English1,,0,0,0,,And at its heart lies a deep paradox.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.64,0:03:53.32,English1,,0,0,0,,In the forest, no matter what direction I point my torch,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.32,0:03:56.36,English1,,0,0,0,,the beam will always hit the trunk of a tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.80,0:04:00.88,English1,,0,0,0,,And just as everywhere I look I see a tree,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.88,0:04:03.44,English1,,0,0,0,,if the universe is sufficiently large,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.44,0:04:08.36,English1,,0,0,0,,then every line of sight from Earth should end in a star.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.36,0:04:10.96,English1,,0,0,0,,The night sky shouldn't be black at all,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.96,0:04:13.08,English1,,0,0,0,,it should be ablaze with starlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.40,0:04:19.20,English1,,0,0,0,,First posed in the 1570s,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.20,0:04:23.36,English1,,0,0,0,,this question would become known as Olbers' Paradox.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.92,0:04:29.84,English1,,0,0,0,,One possible solution was that the Earth was surrounded
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.84,0:04:34.80,English1,,0,0,0,,by dark stuff that obscured our view of the stars behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.80,0:04:39.16,English1,,0,0,0,,But it was soon realised that these dark clouds would absorb
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.16,0:04:43.28,English1,,0,0,0,,the light from the stars, heat up and eventually glow
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.28,0:04:46.04,English1,,0,0,0,,with the same brightness as the stars they obscured.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.60,0:04:57.08,English1,,0,0,0,,The paradox was only satisfactorily explained in the 20th century.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.00,0:05:03.16,English1,,0,0,0,,The answer - the reason it gets dark at night
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.16,0:05:06.64,English1,,0,0,0,,is because the universe had a beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.64,0:05:11.28,English1,,0,0,0,,It began with the big bang 13.8 billion years ago, and so
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.28,0:05:13.58,English1,,0,0,0,,we only see those stars
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.58,0:05:16.28,English1,,0,0,0,,whose light has had time to reach us since then.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.28,0:05:19.88,English1,,0,0,0,,The sky is dark because light from the most distant stars
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.88,0:05:21.68,English1,,0,0,0,,hasn't got here yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.96,0:05:34.32,English1,,0,0,0,,No mysterious stuff was needed to block out the light.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.32,0:05:38.24,English1,,0,0,0,,The dark spaces that starlight had yet to reach were empty,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.24,0:05:41.68,English1,,0,0,0,,and cosmologists could sleep easy at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.52,0:05:46.64,English1,,0,0,0,,But before long, we began to see hints that there might be
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.64,0:05:49.20,English1,,0,0,0,,more out there than meets the eye,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.20,0:05:52.56,English1,,0,0,0,,that the shadowy recesses of empty space
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.56,0:05:55.08,English1,,0,0,0,,might not be so empty after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.24,0:06:00.84,English1,,0,0,0,,The first clues had in fact begun to emerge from the gloom
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.84,0:06:04.16,English1,,0,0,0,,some 200 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.16,0:06:07.92,English1,,0,0,0,,not in the depths of the universe, but in our own back yard.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.04,0:06:23.32,English1,,0,0,0,,The invention of the telescope in the 17th century had allowed us
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.32,0:06:27.56,English1,,0,0,0,,to see the dimmest light from the deepest reaches of the solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.92,0:06:34.40,English1,,0,0,0,,And in 1781, it had revealed a seventh planet, Uranus,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.40,0:06:37.24,English1,,0,0,0,,the first to be found since ancient times.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.96,0:06:42.16,English1,,0,0,0,,But there was something odd about this new planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.16,0:06:46.72,English1,,0,0,0,,Astronomers found that as time passed, Uranus's actual position
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.72,0:06:50.08,English1,,0,0,0,,was drifting further and further away from the position
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.08,0:06:53.20,English1,,0,0,0,,the laws of gravity predicted it should be at.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.20,0:06:57.08,English1,,0,0,0,,One explanation was that the laws themselves were wrong,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.08,0:06:59.20,English1,,0,0,0,,but working at the Paris Observatory,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.20,0:07:02.08,English1,,0,0,0,,one man came up with a different solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.08,0:07:04.08,English1,,0,0,0,,There was something else out there,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.08,0:07:08.16,English1,,0,0,0,,something we couldn't see that was interfering with Uranus's orbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.28,0:07:23.52,English1,,0,0,0,,In 1846, the mathematician Urbain Le Verrier
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.52,0:07:28.32,English1,,0,0,0,,was employed at the observatory to calculate the orbits of comets
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.32,0:07:30.60,English1,,0,0,0,,as they wandered through the solar system...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.32,0:07:36.52,English1,,0,0,0,,..and predict when they would light up the night sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.56,0:07:43.96,English1,,0,0,0,,Le Verrier has been described as having an almost pathological
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.96,0:07:48.28,English1,,0,0,0,,need to impose order on everything and everyone around him,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.28,0:07:51.76,English1,,0,0,0,,and to have made no allowances for human error or frailty.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.48,0:07:56.04,English1,,0,0,0,,When asked what he was like, a colleague remarked,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.04,0:07:58.72,English1,,0,0,0,,"I do not know whether Monsieur Le Verrier is actually
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.72,0:08:01.04,English1,,0,0,0,,"the most detestable man in France,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.04,0:08:04.44,English1,,0,0,0,,"but I am quite certain that he is the most detested."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.28,0:08:09.04,English1,,0,0,0,,But he was undoubtedly a mathematical genius,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.04,0:08:11.80,English1,,0,0,0,,and he was as harsh on himself as he was on others.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.04,0:08:17.88,English1,,0,0,0,,And because he was a mathematician, he set about finding the object
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.88,0:08:22.40,English1,,0,0,0,,he thought was influencing Uranus not by scouring the skies
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.40,0:08:27.16,English1,,0,0,0,,with a telescope, but by determining its position through calculation.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.32,0:08:41.20,English1,,0,0,0,,These are Le Verrier's original hand-written notes from 1846.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.20,0:08:42.36,English1,,0,0,0,,This one is called
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.36,0:08:45.92,English1,,0,0,0,,"Searches of the disturbing body. Second approximation."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.08,0:08:52.48,English1,,0,0,0,,It contains page after page
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.48,0:08:55.16,English1,,0,0,0,,of complicated mathematical calculations.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.88,0:09:08.44,English1,,0,0,0,,What Le Verrier was attempting was quite different
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.44,0:09:10.64,English1,,0,0,0,,to what was normally done in astronomy,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.64,0:09:12.84,English1,,0,0,0,,where you know where an object is -
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.84,0:09:17.80,English1,,0,0,0,,say a star or planet or comet - you then use the laws of gravity
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.80,0:09:22.04,English1,,0,0,0,,to explain its effects on nearby objects.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.04,0:09:25.28,English1,,0,0,0,,Here, he didn't know where his disturbing body was.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.28,0:09:30.04,English1,,0,0,0,,All he had to go by was the effect it had on the orbit of Uranus.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.04,0:09:34.20,English1,,0,0,0,,So he made some starting assumptions about its position, and then
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.20,0:09:39.08,English1,,0,0,0,,carried out a calculation to predict the effect it would have on Uranus.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.08,0:09:42.08,English1,,0,0,0,,He then compared that with what had been observed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.08,0:09:45.68,English1,,0,0,0,,When the two didn't match, he went back and adjusted
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.68,0:09:48.96,English1,,0,0,0,,his starting assumptions and repeated the calculation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.76,0:09:53.04,English1,,0,0,0,,He did this again and again
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.04,0:09:55.96,English1,,0,0,0,,until his prediction matched the observation.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.12,0:10:04.56,English1,,0,0,0,,On the 31st of August, 1846,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.56,0:10:07.60,English1,,0,0,0,,after three months of painstaking work,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.60,0:10:11.08,English1,,0,0,0,,Le Verrier presented his results to the French Academy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.08,0:10:13.80,English1,,0,0,0,,He announced that his calculations had revealed
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.80,0:10:16.72,English1,,0,0,0,,what he believed was a new planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.72,0:10:20.32,English1,,0,0,0,,and, crucially, that he had the co-ordinates in the night sky
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.32,0:10:22.68,English1,,0,0,0,,that showed where it could be found.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.16,0:10:30.36,English1,,0,0,0,,And yet, despite this, he was unable to persuade
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.36,0:10:33.48,English1,,0,0,0,,any French astronomers to search for his planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.12,0:10:41.20,English1,,0,0,0,,Eventually, Le Verrier sent his calculations
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.20,0:10:44.48,English1,,0,0,0,,to Johann Galle at the Berlin Observatory.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.48,0:10:47.80,English1,,0,0,0,,His letter arrived on the 23rd of September,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.80,0:10:50.76,English1,,0,0,0,,and the new planet was found the same evening
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.76,0:10:54.80,English1,,0,0,0,,within one degree of Le Verrier's predicted location.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.80,0:10:57.56,English1,,0,0,0,,His calculations were so precise,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.56,0:11:00.92,English1,,0,0,0,,it took Galle less than an hour to find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.04,0:11:11.80,English1,,0,0,0,,Le Verrier and Galle had discovered the planet Neptune.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.96,0:11:17.44,English1,,0,0,0,,A vast ice giant, 17 times heavier than the Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.44,0:11:20.00,English1,,0,0,0,,and nearly 60 times its volume,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.00,0:11:24.40,English1,,0,0,0,,lurking in the shadows some 4 billion kilometres from the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.92,0:11:33.04,English1,,0,0,0,,Neptune had been hard to find
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.04,0:11:36.24,English1,,0,0,0,,not because there was anything inherently mysterious about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.24,0:11:40.08,English1,,0,0,0,,It's dark simply because it's so far from the sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.08,0:11:42.96,English1,,0,0,0,,there's precious little light to illuminate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.56,0:11:46.76,English1,,0,0,0,,And outside our solar system,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.76,0:11:50.44,English1,,0,0,0,,this lack of illumination is an even bigger problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.16,0:11:56.16,English1,,0,0,0,,And it means even more stuff is hidden in the dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.28,0:12:04.08,English1,,0,0,0,,Stars are thought to contain just 11% of the atoms in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.08,0:12:08.72,English1,,0,0,0,,The rest - clouds of gas and dust, planets, dead stars -
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.72,0:12:12.20,English1,,0,0,0,,we can't see, because they give off hardly any light.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.28,0:12:17.40,English1,,0,0,0,,The dark spaces between the stars aren't empty at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.40,0:12:20.16,English1,,0,0,0,,In fact, they contain the vast majority
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.16,0:12:22.04,English1,,0,0,0,,of the stuff that's out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.84,0:12:30.92,English1,,0,0,0,,Up until the middle of the 20th century, most astronomers
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.92,0:12:36.00,English1,,0,0,0,,believed that, although they couldn't see nearly 90% of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.00,0:12:39.44,English1,,0,0,0,,the universe was still, theoretically at least,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.44,0:12:40.84,English1,,0,0,0,,entirely visible.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.68,0:12:45.76,English1,,0,0,0,,But that was about to change.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.16,0:12:51.36,English1,,0,0,0,,Welcome to White Sands Missile Range.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.92,0:13:03.76,English1,,0,0,0,,In 1964, NASA scientists fitted an Aerobee rocket
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.76,0:13:06.00,English1,,0,0,0,,with an X-ray detector...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.00,0:13:07.72,English1,,0,0,0,,'..two, one...'
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.96,0:13:12.88,English1,,0,0,0,,..and blasted it to the edge of space.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.28,0:13:18.72,English1,,0,0,0,,High above the X-ray-absorbing layers of the atmosphere,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.72,0:13:21.72,English1,,0,0,0,,the detector spotted something extremely bright
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.72,0:13:24.20,English1,,0,0,0,,in the constellation of Cygnus.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.80,0:13:32.52,English1,,0,0,0,,The young British astronomer Paul Murdin was fascinated by this
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.52,0:13:36.08,English1,,0,0,0,,mysterious X-ray source, known as Cygnus X-1.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.08,0:13:38.48,English1,,0,0,0,,And when he joined the Royal Greenwich Observatory
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.48,0:13:40.36,English1,,0,0,0,,in the summer of 1971,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.36,0:13:43.60,English1,,0,0,0,,he was given with the perfect opportunity to discover what it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.56,0:13:48.16,English1,,0,0,0,,It was known that X-rays were produced
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.16,0:13:53.04,English1,,0,0,0,,when gas was heated to temperatures upwards of a million degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.04,0:13:54.80,English1,,0,0,0,,DOORBELL CHIMES
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.80,0:13:56.56,English1,,0,0,0,,Hello, Paul!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.56,0:14:00.20,English1,,0,0,0,,'But no-one knew for sure what could produce such extreme
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.20,0:14:02.24,English1,,0,0,0,,'conditions out in space.'
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.76,0:14:06.76,English1,,0,0,0,,What was it about X-ray sources that interested you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.76,0:14:10.08,English1,,0,0,0,,Celestial X-ray sources had just been discovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.08,0:14:13.12,English1,,0,0,0,,They were places in the sky where X-rays came from.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.12,0:14:14.72,English1,,0,0,0,,It's a very energetic radiation,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.72,0:14:17.60,English1,,0,0,0,,it means something really powerful is happening there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.60,0:14:21.12,English1,,0,0,0,,I mean, the X-rays are a flag which the star is waving at you,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.12,0:14:24.84,English1,,0,0,0,,saying, "Look at me, look at me, look at me - I'm really interesting."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.04,0:14:30.64,English1,,0,0,0,,But when Paul trained his optical telescope on the source,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.64,0:14:34.24,English1,,0,0,0,,all he saw was an ordinary, everyday star,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.24,0:14:37.28,English1,,0,0,0,,nowhere near hot enough to produce X-rays.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.00,0:14:42.52,English1,,0,0,0,,Most stars are in systems where there's two stars,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.52,0:14:45.04,English1,,0,0,0,,three stars, even five stars or many more.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.04,0:14:49.24,English1,,0,0,0,,It's really unusual to have a star like our sun that's on its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.24,0:14:51.32,English1,,0,0,0,,I decided therefore that I'd try
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.32,0:14:54.72,English1,,0,0,0,,and look for evidence on the star that I could see, that there
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.72,0:14:58.44,English1,,0,0,0,,was another star nearby and that they were circling one another.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.44,0:15:02.32,English1,,0,0,0,,By recording its motion night after night, Paul discovered
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.32,0:15:08.36,English1,,0,0,0,,the star was orbiting an invisible partner, once every 5.6 days.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.36,0:15:12.92,English1,,0,0,0,,What you can calculate, once you know the period of a binary star,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.92,0:15:18.44,English1,,0,0,0,,is the mass of the system and the mass of the component parts of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.44,0:15:20.44,English1,,0,0,0,,And so, that was the thing to do next.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.44,0:15:23.08,English1,,0,0,0,,And then, maybe within an hour,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.08,0:15:27.76,English1,,0,0,0,,I knew that the star which I couldn't see
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.76,0:15:31.04,English1,,0,0,0,,was four solar masses or more.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.80,0:15:37.64,English1,,0,0,0,,Something that heavy so close to the star he could see
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.64,0:15:40.88,English1,,0,0,0,,would strip material from its outer layers, the immense
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.88,0:15:46.80,English1,,0,0,0,,frictional forces heating the gas to such an extent it produced X-rays.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.60,0:15:54.12,English1,,0,0,0,,But physicists only knew of one object that could be that massive
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.12,0:15:57.28,English1,,0,0,0,,and yet remain completely invisible.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.28,0:16:00.56,English1,,0,0,0,,It was something that had only ever existed in theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.80,0:16:05.72,English1,,0,0,0,,Paul Murdin had discovered the first black hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.16,0:16:12.88,English1,,0,0,0,,I was just... I was just elated.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.88,0:16:17.20,English1,,0,0,0,,And I had to get up from my desk and walk about a bit to calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.20,0:16:19.00,English1,,0,0,0,,My pulse raced.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.00,0:16:23.12,English1,,0,0,0,,I knew it was big, but I was also a little bit frightened of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.12,0:16:24.88,English1,,0,0,0,,so I knew I had to check it very carefully
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.88,0:16:30.08,English1,,0,0,0,,and go through it all again and check what I was doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.08,0:16:31.80,English1,,0,0,0,,But it was... It was a great hour
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.80,0:16:35.00,English1,,0,0,0,,and I couldn't really do any serious work for the rest of the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.12,0:16:39.24,English1,,0,0,0,,And I felt... I felt really happy with myself, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.72,0:16:45.36,English1,,0,0,0,,Thanks to Paul Murdin,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.36,0:16:50.36,English1,,0,0,0,,the universe now had a new and profoundly dark inhabitant.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.28,0:16:55.92,English1,,0,0,0,,Black holes are so incredibly dense,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.92,0:17:00.16,English1,,0,0,0,,their gravity warps the fabric of space and time around them
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.16,0:17:05.16,English1,,0,0,0,,to such an extent that nothing, not even light, can escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.08,0:17:15.00,English1,,0,0,0,,As you approach a black hole,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.00,0:17:17.20,English1,,0,0,0,,an observer watching you from a distance
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.20,0:17:21.52,English1,,0,0,0,,will see the light coming from you getting redder and redder.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.52,0:17:24.60,English1,,0,0,0,,And you will appear to be moving in slow motion
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.60,0:17:28.40,English1,,0,0,0,,as the immense gravitational field of the black hole
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.40,0:17:31.76,English1,,0,0,0,,stretches both space and time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.76,0:17:35.52,English1,,0,0,0,,And then, as you pass through the event horizon,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.52,0:17:39.44,English1,,0,0,0,,the point of no return that marks the edge of a black hole,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.44,0:17:44.48,English1,,0,0,0,,you simply disappear, lost from the universe for ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.76,0:17:58.20,English1,,0,0,0,,Black holes are objects that would remain dark
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.20,0:18:01.04,English1,,0,0,0,,no matter how much light you shone on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.12,0:18:07.12,English1,,0,0,0,,Through their effects on other things,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.12,0:18:10.96,English1,,0,0,0,,we've now discovered dozens of black holes in our own galaxy,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.96,0:18:14.04,English1,,0,0,0,,and estimate there must be billions upon billions
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.04,0:18:16.16,English1,,0,0,0,,of them throughout the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.16,0:18:19.44,English1,,0,0,0,,Including huge, supermassive black holes
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.44,0:18:22.20,English1,,0,0,0,,millions of times the mass of the sun
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.20,0:18:25.00,English1,,0,0,0,,at the heart of nearly every galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.40,0:18:36.52,English1,,0,0,0,,As strange as black holes are,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.52,0:18:40.24,English1,,0,0,0,,they were at least something we'd expected to find.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.12,0:18:44.88,English1,,0,0,0,,We had theories that predicted their existence
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.88,0:18:46.96,English1,,0,0,0,,and described their properties.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.96,0:18:51.92,English1,,0,0,0,,But since the 1930s,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.92,0:18:56.72,English1,,0,0,0,,astronomers had seen disturbing hints of something much stranger.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.84,0:19:04.20,English1,,0,0,0,,Stuff that was both completely invisible and completely unexpected.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.40,0:19:10.96,English1,,0,0,0,,FAINT WHISPERING
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.12,0:19:18.52,English1,,0,0,0,,As a child, Vera Rubin spent hours awake at night
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.52,0:19:21.32,English1,,0,0,0,,staring out of the window above her bed,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.32,0:19:24.64,English1,,0,0,0,,gazing at the stars as they moved across the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.68,0:19:31.56,English1,,0,0,0,,Then, in her 30s and a mother herself,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.56,0:19:34.48,English1,,0,0,0,,she decided to realise her childhood dream
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.48,0:19:37.52,English1,,0,0,0,,and embark on a career as an astronomer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.52,0:19:39.28,English1,,0,0,0,,FAINT WHISPERING
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.60,0:19:52.04,English1,,0,0,0,,In the mid 1960s, the hottest topic in astronomy was quasars.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.88,0:19:57.52,English1,,0,0,0,,But the field was extremely crowded
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.52,0:20:01.24,English1,,0,0,0,,and because the biggest telescopes that were needed to study them
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.24,0:20:03.76,English1,,0,0,0,,were often in the remotest parts of the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.76,0:20:08.32,English1,,0,0,0,,working on quasars meant a lot of time spent away from home.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.32,0:20:10.76,English1,,0,0,0,,So Vera needed to find a research topic
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.76,0:20:14.08,English1,,0,0,0,,that was more compatible with being a working mum,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.08,0:20:17.60,English1,,0,0,0,,and a smaller field where she could really make her mark.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.00,0:20:29.04,English1,,0,0,0,,So she began a project measuring the way stars move within galaxies
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.04,0:20:31.04,English1,,0,0,0,,like our own Milky Way.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.80,0:20:59.16,English1,,0,0,0,,- Whoa! - HE LAUGHS
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.88,0:21:10.24,English1,,0,0,0,,Everything in a galaxy is on the move and rotating.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.24,0:21:13.04,English1,,0,0,0,,In one minute, the Earth travels
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.04,0:21:16.36,English1,,0,0,0,,nearly 2,000 kilometres around the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.16,0:21:23.04,English1,,0,0,0,,But in that same time, the sun and the entire solar system
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.04,0:21:28.80,English1,,0,0,0,,travel 12,000 kilometres around the centre of the Milky Way galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.60,0:21:33.88,English1,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.88,0:21:35.80,English1,,0,0,0,,I'm not liking this!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.08,0:21:45.56,English1,,0,0,0,,If you think this is spinning fast, think about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.56,0:21:50.04,English1,,0,0,0,,The Earth is travelling around the sun at 108,000 kilometres an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.04,0:21:55.24,English1,,0,0,0,,Ha! And the sun and the entire solar system
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.24,0:21:59.08,English1,,0,0,0,,are travelling at 720,000 kilometres an hour
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.08,0:22:01.52,English1,,0,0,0,,around the centre of the galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.52,0:22:03.20,English1,,0,0,0,,HE LAUGHS
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.44,0:22:09.48,English1,,0,0,0,,Can we stop it now?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.08,0:22:22.48,English1,,0,0,0,,That's done me in, that really has.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.48,0:22:24.24,English1,,0,0,0,,Thanks very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.04,0:22:33.16,English1,,0,0,0,,But when Vera Rubin measured the speed of stars
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.16,0:22:35.68,English1,,0,0,0,,orbiting the centre of the Andromeda Galaxy,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.68,0:22:38.56,English1,,0,0,0,,she found something deeply puzzling.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.64,0:22:45.28,English1,,0,0,0,,If I plot a graph of the speed
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.28,0:22:48.44,English1,,0,0,0,,at which planets in our solar system orbit the sun
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.44,0:22:51.36,English1,,0,0,0,,against their distance from the sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.36,0:22:57.16,English1,,0,0,0,,I find that the closest planet, Mercury, orbits the fastest.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.16,0:23:03.32,English1,,0,0,0,,It's then followed by Venus, Earth, Mars and so on.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.32,0:23:07.52,English1,,0,0,0,,The further out you go...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.52,0:23:09.52,English1,,0,0,0,,the slower the orbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.52,0:23:13.56,English1,,0,0,0,,In fact, Neptune moves so slowly relative to the other planets
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.56,0:23:16.36,English1,,0,0,0,,and has so far to go in orbit around the sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.36,0:23:19.08,English1,,0,0,0,,that it's only completed one full circuit
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.08,0:23:21.64,English1,,0,0,0,,since it was discovered 167 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.16,0:23:28.52,English1,,0,0,0,,Now, if I plot the same graph again of speed against distance,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.52,0:23:31.12,English1,,0,0,0,,but this time, the speed
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.12,0:23:34.64,English1,,0,0,0,,at which the stars orbit the centre of a galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.64,0:23:36.56,English1,,0,0,0,,against their distance from the centre,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.56,0:23:39.28,English1,,0,0,0,,I'd expect to see for the outer stars,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.28,0:23:43.20,English1,,0,0,0,,that the speed drops off with distance, as it did for the planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.20,0:23:46.64,English1,,0,0,0,,But when Vera Rubin plotted her data,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.64,0:23:49.12,English1,,0,0,0,,she found that the further out you went,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.12,0:23:52.28,English1,,0,0,0,,the speed of the stars didn't drop off,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.28,0:23:54.96,English1,,0,0,0,,it remained roughly the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.84,0:23:59.84,English1,,0,0,0,,The planets move more slowly the further out they are
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.84,0:24:01.68,English1,,0,0,0,,because the further you go,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.68,0:24:04.96,English1,,0,0,0,,the weaker the sun's gravitational field becomes.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.96,0:24:10.32,English1,,0,0,0,,So anything moving too fast would simply fly off into outer space.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.32,0:24:13.04,English1,,0,0,0,,But Vera Rubin's result for galaxies
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.04,0:24:15.96,English1,,0,0,0,,suggested there must be an extra source of gravity
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.96,0:24:19.56,English1,,0,0,0,,holding all those fast-moving stars in their orbits.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.44,0:24:25.40,English1,,0,0,0,,This extra gravity was needed
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.40,0:24:29.08,English1,,0,0,0,,because when astronomers added up the gravitational pull
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.08,0:24:33.20,English1,,0,0,0,,of all the dark things they thought might be lurking in the galaxy,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.20,0:24:37.00,English1,,0,0,0,,planets, clouds of dust, even black holes,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.00,0:24:40.24,English1,,0,0,0,,it always came out about ten times less
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.24,0:24:42.16,English1,,0,0,0,,than that needed to account for
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.16,0:24:44.92,English1,,0,0,0,,the stellar speeds Vera Rubin had measured.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.76,0:24:49.00,English1,,0,0,0,,There were two possible explanations.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.00,0:24:52.36,English1,,0,0,0,,Either Einstein's theory of gravity was wrong,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.36,0:24:56.48,English1,,0,0,0,,or galaxies were full of a completely new kind of stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.48,0:24:58.36,English1,,0,0,0,,Something that wasn't made of atoms,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.36,0:25:01.68,English1,,0,0,0,,was completely invisible and very heavy.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.68,0:25:03.84,English1,,0,0,0,,A new form of dark matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.84,0:25:06.68,English1,,0,0,0,,Something astronomers named... dark matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.24,0:25:23.80,English1,,0,0,0,,Unsurprisingly, rather than accept
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.80,0:25:28.08,English1,,0,0,0,,that galaxies were full of some mysterious unseen stuff,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.08,0:25:31.88,English1,,0,0,0,,some physicists once again thought tweaking the laws of gravity
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.88,0:25:33.76,English1,,0,0,0,,might be the simplest solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.68,0:25:40.52,English1,,0,0,0,,That was until astronomers captured an astonishing image.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.60,0:25:43.28,English1,,0,0,0,,For me, this is one of the most
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.28,0:25:45.64,English1,,0,0,0,,amazing pictures in modern astronomy.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.64,0:25:50.96,English1,,0,0,0,,It's an image of a cluster of galaxies called the Bullet Cluster.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.96,0:25:54.12,English1,,0,0,0,,It gets its name from this bullet-shaped cloud of gas,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.12,0:25:58.96,English1,,0,0,0,,which is actually a shockwave caused by the collision
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.96,0:26:03.48,English1,,0,0,0,,not of just clouds of gas or stars or even whole galaxies,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.48,0:26:06.80,English1,,0,0,0,,but clusters of galaxies coming together
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.80,0:26:11.04,English1,,0,0,0,,and passing through each other at 10-million kilometres an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.48,0:26:18.68,English1,,0,0,0,,It almost gives me vertigo trying to imagine the immensity of the scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.12,0:26:23.56,English1,,0,0,0,,But it's not the magnitude of the collision
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.56,0:26:26.00,English1,,0,0,0,,that makes this image so important.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.00,0:26:29.48,English1,,0,0,0,,It's what it did to the clusters' constituent parts.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.84,0:26:33.12,English1,,0,0,0,,As the clusters came together,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.12,0:26:35.12,English1,,0,0,0,,the stars and planets in the galaxies
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.12,0:26:37.04,English1,,0,0,0,,pretty much passed through each other
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.04,0:26:40.88,English1,,0,0,0,,because although they're big, the distances between them are so vast
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.88,0:26:45.36,English1,,0,0,0,,that the chances of any two stars colliding is actually very small.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.36,0:26:48.12,English1,,0,0,0,,But that doesn't apply to the dust and gas
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.12,0:26:53.40,English1,,0,0,0,,that makes up 90% by mass of all the stuff we can see in a galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.40,0:26:57.24,English1,,0,0,0,,When these collide, they create a huge, hot cloud -
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.24,0:27:00.20,English1,,0,0,0,,these two pink regions in the centre of the image.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.60,0:27:05.16,English1,,0,0,0,,But if most of the mass is trapped here in the clouds,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.16,0:27:09.08,English1,,0,0,0,,then you'd expect most of the gravity to be centred there, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.08,0:27:11.04,English1,,0,0,0,,But that's not what you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.04,0:27:15.72,English1,,0,0,0,,These outer blue regions show where light has been bent round
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.72,0:27:19.80,English1,,0,0,0,,as gravity warps the fabric of space itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.80,0:27:23.44,English1,,0,0,0,,That means most of the gravity is centred out here,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.44,0:27:25.60,English1,,0,0,0,,rather than in the middle.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.60,0:27:28.28,English1,,0,0,0,,The simplest way to explain this
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.28,0:27:30.80,English1,,0,0,0,,is that it wasn't just stars and planets
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.80,0:27:33.64,English1,,0,0,0,,that passed through as the clusters collided,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.64,0:27:35.36,English1,,0,0,0,,something else did, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.36,0:27:38.28,English1,,0,0,0,,Something massive, yet invisible.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.28,0:27:41.92,English1,,0,0,0,,This image is the best evidence we have yet
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.92,0:27:43.76,English1,,0,0,0,,for the existence of dark matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.48,0:27:55.08,English1,,0,0,0,,It's now generally accepted that dark matter is real,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.08,0:27:59.24,English1,,0,0,0,,which means there's far more stuff in the universe than we'd thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.00,0:28:02.96,English1,,0,0,0,,In fact, there's four times
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.96,0:28:06.24,English1,,0,0,0,,as much dark matter as there is normal matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.84,0:28:13.64,English1,,0,0,0,,And so vast swathes of the universe are not just unseen,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.64,0:28:16.44,English1,,0,0,0,,they're fundamentally unseeable.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.08,0:28:20.12,English1,,0,0,0,,The reason dark matter is so elusive
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.12,0:28:24.60,English1,,0,0,0,,is because it doesn't reflect light and it doesn't emit light.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.60,0:28:27.24,English1,,0,0,0,,So we can't see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.24,0:28:31.04,English1,,0,0,0,,And worse than that, what gives normal matter its solidity
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.04,0:28:33.56,English1,,0,0,0,,is the electromagnetic force.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.56,0:28:36.68,English1,,0,0,0,,And dark matter particles don't feel that force,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.68,0:28:39.32,English1,,0,0,0,,so they just pass straight through matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.32,0:28:43.56,English1,,0,0,0,,The only hope we have is if they hit an atomic nucleus head-on.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.56,0:28:47.44,English1,,0,0,0,,And even if they do, that's really hard to detect.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.72,0:28:54.20,English1,,0,0,0,,And so the hunt for dark matter
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.20,0:28:59.56,English1,,0,0,0,,has turned from the incredibly large to the unimaginably small.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.80,0:29:07.36,English1,,0,0,0,,From scouring the skies with telescopes
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.36,0:29:10.20,English1,,0,0,0,,to detectors buried deep underground.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.56,0:29:13.80,English1,,0,0,0,,When it comes to the search for dark matter,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.80,0:29:17.44,English1,,0,0,0,,the place I'm going to is pretty much the centre of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.56,0:29:27.00,English1,,0,0,0,,The Gran Sasso National Laboratory
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.00,0:29:31.20,English1,,0,0,0,,lies beneath almost a kilometre and a half of solid rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.16,0:29:36.44,English1,,0,0,0,,And can only be reached through a tunnel
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.44,0:29:39.00,English1,,0,0,0,,cut deep into the Italian Apennines.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.24,0:29:47.60,English1,,0,0,0,,The reason you'd build a laboratory underneath a mountain
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.60,0:29:52.52,English1,,0,0,0,,is because our planet is constantly being bombarded by cosmic rays.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.52,0:29:54.96,English1,,0,0,0,,These collide with the upper atmosphere,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.96,0:29:57.24,English1,,0,0,0,,creating a cascade of particles
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.24,0:30:00.16,English1,,0,0,0,,that shower down onto the surface of the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.16,0:30:05.72,English1,,0,0,0,,The rock above me effectively forms a 1400-metre-thick roof
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.72,0:30:08.72,English1,,0,0,0,,that absorbs most of these particles,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.72,0:30:12.20,English1,,0,0,0,,shielding and protecting the equipment below.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.20,0:30:14.92,English1,,0,0,0,,But crucially for dark-matter hunters,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.92,0:30:17.16,English1,,0,0,0,,it passes straight through normal matter,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.16,0:30:18.48,English1,,0,0,0,,straight through the rock,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.48,0:30:20.92,English1,,0,0,0,,and the hope is, into their detectors.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.16,0:30:28.36,English1,,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.36,0:30:30.76,English1,,0,0,0,,It looks like a Bond villain's evil lair.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.12,0:31:03.84,English1,,0,0,0,,Gran Sasso is the world's largest underground laboratory.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.60,0:31:11.36,English1,,0,0,0,,And for the last ten years,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.36,0:31:15.36,English1,,0,0,0,,it's been home to dark matter scientists like Dr Chamkaur Ghag,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.36,0:31:18.12,English1,,0,0,0,,who works on DarkSide-50,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.12,0:31:21.36,English1,,0,0,0,,one of five dark matter experiments based here.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.92,0:31:34.20,English1,,0,0,0,,- So hairnet.  - Hairnet.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.20,0:31:36.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,Or head net, in my case.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.60,0:31:43.60,English1,,0,0,0,,- Milligram levels of dust can destroy the experiment. - Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.96,0:32:02.16,English1,,0,0,0,,That looks very impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.16,0:32:03.76,English1,,0,0,0,,- Yep. - Very sci-fi.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.68,0:32:10.96,English1,,0,0,0,,So tell me, how does the experiment work?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.96,0:32:13.68,English1,,0,0,0,,Well, the entire experiment is configured like a Russian doll,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.68,0:32:16.36,English1,,0,0,0,,where the first outer layer is the mountain itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.36,0:32:19.96,English1,,0,0,0,,protecting the experiment from radiation from space.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.96,0:32:22.52,English1,,0,0,0,,Then we have this tank that we're standing in.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.52,0:32:25.12,English1,,0,0,0,,And this tank is going to be flooded full of water.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.12,0:32:27.12,English1,,0,0,0,,What, the whole cylinder?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.12,0:32:29.84,English1,,0,0,0,,Absolutely. This is all completely filled to the brim.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.84,0:32:33.08,English1,,0,0,0,,About 750 cubic metres of water will fill this thing
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.08,0:32:37.04,English1,,0,0,0,,to stop radiation coming from the laboratory and the rock around us.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.04,0:32:40.36,English1,,0,0,0,,That's protecting this huge metal sphere right here,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.36,0:32:42.16,English1,,0,0,0,,which is the final layer of protection
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.16,0:32:45.32,English1,,0,0,0,,before we get to DarkSide itself, which is inside there right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.32,0:32:47.76,English1,,0,0,0,,That's the detector, that's the heart of the experiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.76,0:32:50.00,English1,,0,0,0,,That's the thing that will be detecting dark matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.20,0:32:55.20,English1,,0,0,0,,- You haven't got a light switch up there. - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.20,0:32:57.20,English1,,0,0,0,,I'm going to get up there and have a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.36,0:33:06.84,English1,,0,0,0,,DarkSide-50 is designed to detect
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.84,0:33:09.44,English1,,0,0,0,,a new class of fundamental particles
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.44,0:33:12.72,English1,,0,0,0,,called weakly interacting massive particles.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.04,0:33:17.72,English1,,0,0,0,,Predicted by theory, it's thought that these WIMPs
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.72,0:33:21.00,English1,,0,0,0,,might be the stuff of which dark matter is made.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.28,0:33:27.68,English1,,0,0,0,,So that metal sphere in the centre, that's DarkSide?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.68,0:33:30.80,English1,,0,0,0,,That's right. That's a detector full of 150kg of liquid argon.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.80,0:33:32.44,English1,,0,0,0,,Dark matter particles should be
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.44,0:33:34.76,English1,,0,0,0,,streaming through the detector all the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.76,0:33:36.88,English1,,0,0,0,,but most of them just go straight through
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.88,0:33:39.44,English1,,0,0,0,,because they're very weakly interacting particles.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.44,0:33:42.80,English1,,0,0,0,,If we're lucky, one will collide with the nucleus of an argon atom,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.80,0:33:45.56,English1,,0,0,0,,producing flashes of light that the detector will pick up.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.32,0:33:54.24,English1,,0,0,0,,DarkSide is yet to begin its search,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.24,0:33:57.16,English1,,0,0,0,,but elsewhere in the laboratory's labyrinth of tunnels,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.16,0:34:00.76,English1,,0,0,0,,they're already seeing tantalising hints.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.00,0:34:05.60,English1,,0,0,0,,This is the XENON100 experiment that's already running
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.60,0:34:07.44,English1,,0,0,0,,and taking data and has been for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.44,0:34:11.04,English1,,0,0,0,,It's the most sensitive dark matter detector in the world right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.04,0:34:15.00,English1,,0,0,0,,And this is a live feed of dark matter data coming in right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.00,0:34:18.44,English1,,0,0,0,,So, what exactly... What sort of signal or shape are you looking for?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.44,0:34:21.48,English1,,0,0,0,,Well, what we're looking for is an initial flash of light
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.48,0:34:23.32,English1,,0,0,0,,which will be a very sharp peak like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.32,0:34:26.88,English1,,0,0,0,,followed by a much larger peak like that one,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.88,0:34:30.12,English1,,0,0,0,,which is light being generated in a gas layer
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.12,0:34:32.12,English1,,0,0,0,,on top of the liquid xenon.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.12,0:34:34.56,English1,,0,0,0,,Oh. That could be a good one as well, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.56,0:34:35.80,English1,,0,0,0,,There you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.80,0:34:38.08,English1,,0,0,0,,So any one of those events, those spikes,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.08,0:34:39.96,English1,,0,0,0,,could be a dark matter particle?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.96,0:34:42.48,English1,,0,0,0,,That's right. Any one of these events
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.48,0:34:45.40,English1,,0,0,0,,could be the signature of dark matter
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.40,0:34:46.84,English1,,0,0,0,,interacting in XENON100.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.84,0:34:49.72,English1,,0,0,0,,It's just we won't know for sure until the data's been analysed.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.68,0:34:53.72,English1,,0,0,0,,Because it's so sensitive,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.72,0:34:56.56,English1,,0,0,0,,the overwhelming majority of the spikes
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.56,0:34:59.40,English1,,0,0,0,,are due to radiation emitted by the metal
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.40,0:35:01.56,English1,,0,0,0,,that makes up the detector itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.76,0:35:09.32,English1,,0,0,0,,But the hope is experiments like this
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.32,0:35:12.60,English1,,0,0,0,,will definitively detect dark matter particles
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.60,0:35:14.36,English1,,0,0,0,,within the next ten years.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.76,0:35:25.12,English1,,0,0,0,,Today, we think that dark matter not only exists,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.12,0:35:28.40,English1,,0,0,0,,but that it is a vital part of our universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.40,0:35:32.80,English1,,0,0,0,,because without it, the world that we can see wouldn't exist
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.80,0:35:36.80,English1,,0,0,0,,and that's because dark matter not only holds galaxies together,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.80,0:35:41.16,English1,,0,0,0,,it's dark matter that brought the clouds of gas together
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.16,0:35:46.08,English1,,0,0,0,,to form the galaxies in which stars could ignite in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.48,0:35:57.44,English1,,0,0,0,,Dark matter has gone from being a curious quirk
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.44,0:36:01.04,English1,,0,0,0,,of the way stars move around the fringes of galaxies
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.04,0:36:04.56,English1,,0,0,0,,to the reason there are stars and galaxies at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.52,0:36:14.36,English1,,0,0,0,,But in the late 1990s, scientists attempting
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.36,0:36:17.56,English1,,0,0,0,,to measure exactly how much dark matter there was
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.56,0:36:20.16,English1,,0,0,0,,made an astonishing discovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.16,0:36:23.28,English1,,0,0,0,,There was something even more mysterious
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.28,0:36:25.76,English1,,0,0,0,,and even more elusive out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.32,0:36:29.40,English1,,0,0,0,,And to understand what that is,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.40,0:36:34.00,English1,,0,0,0,,you have to go back to the very beginning of everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.00,0:36:36.88,English1,,0,0,0,,The universe began with a gigantic fireball.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.40,0:36:49.00,English1,,0,0,0,,13.8 billion years ago, the universe was born.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.00,0:36:51.52,English1,,0,0,0,,In the so-called big bang,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.52,0:36:54.00,English1,,0,0,0,,everything was created simultaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.24,0:36:58.92,English1,,0,0,0,,See that great flash of light?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.92,0:37:02.84,English1,,0,0,0,,That's all the pieces of the atoms joining together to make a gas.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.84,0:37:05.28,English1,,0,0,0,,And now the gas is getting lumpy.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.28,0:37:07.76,English1,,0,0,0,,It's making the giant galaxies of stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.20,0:37:14.00,English1,,0,0,0,,The expansion of the universe that we now see
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.00,0:37:17.60,English1,,0,0,0,,is just a remnant of the initial violent explosion.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.32,0:37:26.60,English1,,0,0,0,,The big bang means that in the past,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.60,0:37:29.52,English1,,0,0,0,,the universe was much smaller than it is today.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.12,0:37:34.56,English1,,0,0,0,,And it's been getting bigger ever since.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.56,0:37:47.04,English1,,0,0,0,,According to the big bang theory,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.04,0:37:52.32,English1,,0,0,0,,the universe has been expanding for the past 13.8 billion years.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.32,0:37:54.12,English1,,0,0,0,,And for most of that time,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.12,0:37:57.08,English1,,0,0,0,,you'd expect the expansion to be slowing down
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.08,0:37:59.52,English1,,0,0,0,,due to the combined gravitational attraction
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.52,0:38:02.04,English1,,0,0,0,,of all the mass in the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.04,0:38:04.76,English1,,0,0,0,,trying to pull it back together again.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.76,0:38:06.04,English1,,0,0,0,,Now, here's the clever bit,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.04,0:38:08.64,English1,,0,0,0,,Cosmologists realised that by measuring
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.64,0:38:10.92,English1,,0,0,0,,how much the expansion was slowing,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.92,0:38:14.84,English1,,0,0,0,,they could calculate how much stuff was out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.84,0:38:18.68,English1,,0,0,0,,In a sense, it would allow them to weigh the entire universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.40,0:38:25.00,English1,,0,0,0,,But in order to measure how the universe is expanding,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.00,0:38:29.12,English1,,0,0,0,,you need a reliable way to measure distances in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.24,0:38:41.56,English1,,0,0,0,,Something of known brightness, astronomers call a standard candle.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.40,0:38:47.08,English1,,0,0,0,,The flame in this lantern produces a fixed amount of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.08,0:38:51.80,English1,,0,0,0,,It has a specific brightness that I can measure here on the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.80,0:38:55.08,English1,,0,0,0,,But if I let the lantern go, it'll drift away
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.08,0:38:57.84,English1,,0,0,0,,and the light will appear to get dimmer and dimmer
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.84,0:38:59.32,English1,,0,0,0,,the further away it gets.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.60,0:39:04.92,English1,,0,0,0,,Because I know how bright it really is,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.92,0:39:08.16,English1,,0,0,0,,by comparing that with how bright it appears,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.16,0:39:11.00,English1,,0,0,0,,I can calculate how far away it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.00,0:39:36.84,English1,,0,0,0,,And because every lantern's the same,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.84,0:39:39.68,English1,,0,0,0,,I can use the brightness to calculate the distance
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.68,0:39:42.12,English1,,0,0,0,,to any lantern I see in the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.80,0:39:50.92,English1,,0,0,0,,The astronomical equivalent of a Chinese lantern
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.92,0:39:57.44,English1,,0,0,0,,is a particular species of exploding star called a Type 1a supernova.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.00,0:40:16.36,English1,,0,0,0,,These stars always explode when they reach the same critical mass
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.36,0:40:19.80,English1,,0,0,0,,and so always explode with the same brightness.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.88,0:40:25.52,English1,,0,0,0,,So by measuring how bright they appear,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.52,0:40:28.08,English1,,0,0,0,,we can tell how far they are from the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.52,0:40:35.60,English1,,0,0,0,,As well as telling us how far away they are,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.60,0:40:40.52,English1,,0,0,0,,the light reaching us from distant supernovae tells us something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.52,0:40:44.56,English1,,0,0,0,,As it travels across the cosmos, light gets stretched
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.56,0:40:48.40,English1,,0,0,0,,because the space it's travelling through is expanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.40,0:40:53.96,English1,,0,0,0,,And as its wavelength increases, the light gets redder and redder.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.96,0:40:59.40,English1,,0,0,0,,And this red shift tells us how fast the universe was expanding
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.40,0:41:03.48,English1,,0,0,0,,when the light left its source, when the star exploded.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.64,0:41:12.40,English1,,0,0,0,,But when scientists analysed light from the more distant supernovae
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.40,0:41:14.96,English1,,0,0,0,,they found something strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.96,0:41:17.40,English1,,0,0,0,,It was less stretched than expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.68,0:41:21.80,English1,,0,0,0,,It meant that, in the past,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.80,0:41:25.96,English1,,0,0,0,,the universe was expanding more slowly than it is today.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.96,0:41:30.96,English1,,0,0,0,,In other words, the expansion of the universe wasn't slowing down at all,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.96,0:41:32.36,English1,,0,0,0,,it was speeding up.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.12,0:41:41.32,English1,,0,0,0,,The only way the universe's expansion could be accelerating...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.96,0:41:48.52,English1,,0,0,0,,..was if there was a mysterious new force pushing it apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.12,0:41:55.88,English1,,0,0,0,,And just as with dark matter, physicists thought the key
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.88,0:41:58.12,English1,,0,0,0,,to understanding this new force
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.12,0:42:01.36,English1,,0,0,0,,might lie at the smallest possible scales...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.56,0:42:08.48,English1,,0,0,0,,..because quantum physics appeared to provide a ready-made explanation.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.04,0:42:16.24,English1,,0,0,0,,According to quantum field theory, empty space is anything but empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.24,0:42:19.76,English1,,0,0,0,,Particles are constantly appearing and disappearing,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.76,0:42:23.56,English1,,0,0,0,,created out of energy borrowed from the vacuum itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.60,0:42:29.28,English1,,0,0,0,,The hope was that this theoretical vacuum energy
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.28,0:42:33.20,English1,,0,0,0,,might be the very thing that was pushing the universe apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.20,0:42:37.44,English1,,0,0,0,,And the theory allows me to calculate the energy density
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.44,0:42:41.08,English1,,0,0,0,,of the vacuum, that's the amount of energy you'd expect to find
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.08,0:42:42.96,English1,,0,0,0,,in a given volume.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.96,0:42:46.84,English1,,0,0,0,,And so if I take the energy of the vacuum
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.84,0:42:51.60,English1,,0,0,0,,to be a sum over J of half h-bar omega J,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.60,0:42:53.80,English1,,0,0,0,,and if I take the cut-off energy
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.80,0:42:56.72,English1,,0,0,0,,to be of the order of 10 tera electronvolts
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.72,0:42:58.60,English1,,0,0,0,,which is just above the known physics
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.60,0:43:01.88,English1,,0,0,0,,at the Large Hadron Collider, then the formula for the vacuum...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.88,0:43:06.48,English1,,0,0,0,,'All they needed to do was check the energy density the theory predicted
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.48,0:43:11.12,English1,,0,0,0,,'matched that needed to drive the universe's acceleration
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.12,0:43:14.20,English1,,0,0,0,,'and the mysterious force would be explained.'
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.20,0:43:20.92,English1,,0,0,0,,HE MUTTERS EQUATIONS
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.64,0:43:42.56,English1,,0,0,0,,So that would give me a value for the energy density
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.56,0:43:47.96,English1,,0,0,0,,of the vacuum of 10 to the 35 kilograms per cubic metre.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.84,0:43:53.08,English1,,0,0,0,,The trouble is, the value observed by astronomers
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.08,0:43:57.48,English1,,0,0,0,,is 10 to the minus 27 kilograms per cubic metre.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.48,0:44:00.64,English1,,0,0,0,,That means the theoretical number and the experimental number
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.64,0:44:04.72,English1,,0,0,0,,are out by a factor of 10 to the power 62.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.72,0:44:07.64,English1,,0,0,0,,That's one followed by 62 zeros.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.88,0:44:11.40,English1,,0,0,0,,To give you a sense of the scale of the error,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.40,0:44:14.56,English1,,0,0,0,,there've been only 10 to the 17 seconds
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.56,0:44:19.40,English1,,0,0,0,,since the big bang and the diameter of the entire visible universe
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.40,0:44:22.00,English1,,0,0,0,,is 10 to the 27 metres...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.12,0:44:25.64,English1,,0,0,0,,So it's a pretty big error.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.48,0:44:32.72,English1,,0,0,0,,And that meant that whatever was actually pushing the universe apart,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.72,0:44:35.52,English1,,0,0,0,,it was something completely new.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.04,0:44:43.04,English1,,0,0,0,,The truth is, we know very little about what's causing
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.04,0:44:45.76,English1,,0,0,0,,the expansion of the universe to accelerate,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.76,0:44:49.52,English1,,0,0,0,,but we do have a name for it - dark energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.52,0:44:52.08,English1,,0,0,0,,And we know that for it to have the effect that it does,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.08,0:44:54.20,English1,,0,0,0,,there must be an awful lot of it about.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.32,0:45:01.04,English1,,0,0,0,,Einstein's famous equation E=mc^2
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.04,0:45:05.96,English1,,0,0,0,,says that energy and matter are different forms of the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.96,0:45:09.40,English1,,0,0,0,,And the equivalent mass of dark energy dwarfs that
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.40,0:45:11.68,English1,,0,0,0,,of everything else in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.72,0:45:15.96,English1,,0,0,0,,And it means that, today,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.96,0:45:19.88,English1,,0,0,0,,normal matter makes up just 4% of the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.88,0:45:23.28,English1,,0,0,0,,23% of it is elusive dark matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.64,0:45:28.68,English1,,0,0,0,,And a colossal 73% of the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.68,0:45:31.76,English1,,0,0,0,,consists of mysterious dark energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.28,0:45:38.64,English1,,0,0,0,,Just think about it for a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.64,0:45:40.72,English1,,0,0,0,,100 billion galaxies,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.72,0:45:44.60,English1,,0,0,0,,each one containing more than 100 billion stars,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.60,0:45:48.68,English1,,0,0,0,,home in turn to billions upon billions of planets and moons.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.72,0:45:55.88,English1,,0,0,0,,All of that is mere flotsam adrift on a vast and unfathomable ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.88,0:46:00.28,English1,,0,0,0,,Dark matter we can't see and dark energy we can barely comprehend.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.28,0:46:09.92,English1,,0,0,0,,And the very nature of dark energy means the universe is getting
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.92,0:46:12.80,English1,,0,0,0,,more unknowable all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.92,0:46:19.68,English1,,0,0,0,,As space expands and distances become bigger,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.68,0:46:24.04,English1,,0,0,0,,most forces get weaker, because you have the same amount of mass
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.04,0:46:27.80,English1,,0,0,0,,or electric charge, only now everything's further apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.40,0:46:32.88,English1,,0,0,0,,But dark energy behaves completely differently.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.88,0:46:37.44,English1,,0,0,0,,As the universe has expanded, the stronger it's become.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.44,0:46:40.56,English1,,0,0,0,,The more space there is, the more dark energy there is
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.56,0:46:43.88,English1,,0,0,0,,and so the faster the universe expands,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.88,0:46:47.96,English1,,0,0,0,,creating ever more space and ever more dark energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.20,0:46:56.48,English1,,0,0,0,,And that has a profound consequence.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.48,0:46:59.88,English1,,0,0,0,,Just as dark matter pulled the galaxies together
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.88,0:47:02.08,English1,,0,0,0,,to create the cosmos as we know it...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.56,0:47:07.64,English1,,0,0,0,,..so dark energy will tear the universe apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.64,0:47:12.04,English1,,0,0,0,,In the future, as space gets bigger,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.04,0:47:15.32,English1,,0,0,0,,dark energy will become ever more dominant.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.32,0:47:19.08,English1,,0,0,0,,And so it will ultimately shape the universe's destiny.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.08,0:47:22.60,English1,,0,0,0,,And if it continues to increase as it appears to be doing today,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.60,0:47:26.16,English1,,0,0,0,,then it will push the galaxies further and further apart
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.16,0:47:29.36,English1,,0,0,0,,until, eventually, they slip out of view,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.36,0:47:33.40,English1,,0,0,0,,creating a cosmos that will become ever more dark
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.40,0:47:34.80,English1,,0,0,0,,and ever more desolate.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.04,0:47:49.24,English1,,0,0,0,,The ultimate goal of modern cosmology is to understand
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.24,0:47:52.68,English1,,0,0,0,,dark energy and the fate of the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.68,0:47:56.72,English1,,0,0,0,,and to witness how dark matter brought everything together
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.72,0:47:58.12,English1,,0,0,0,,in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.60,0:48:08.40,English1,,0,0,0,,And so to shed light on both the beginning and end of the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.40,0:48:13.08,English1,,0,0,0,,cosmologists have embarked on a quest of epic proportions -
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.08,0:48:18.24,English1,,0,0,0,,to map everywhere in space over the entire lifespan of the cosmos...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.72,0:48:24.68,English1,,0,0,0,,..starting with the darkest period in its past,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.68,0:48:29.36,English1,,0,0,0,,an era that began as the afterglow of the big bang faded away.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.16,0:48:34.32,English1,,0,0,0,,We talk about the ages of the universe in the same way
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.32,0:48:38.24,English1,,0,0,0,,that we talk about the stages in our own lives, from its birth,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.24,0:48:42.52,English1,,0,0,0,,through childhood, adolescence, adulthood and even death.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.52,0:48:45.36,English1,,0,0,0,,So mapping the universe is really about
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.36,0:48:48.16,English1,,0,0,0,,filling in the photo album of its life.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.32,0:48:54.96,English1,,0,0,0,,Here's a picture of me from 20 years ago with my children.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.96,0:48:57.56,English1,,0,0,0,,I know it because I have a lot more hair there.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.56,0:49:01.76,English1,,0,0,0,,And here's a picture of me in my early 20s on graduation.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.76,0:49:03.96,English1,,0,0,0,,And here's one of me as a teenager.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.80,0:49:08.92,English1,,0,0,0,,In the same way, by looking out into space,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.92,0:49:10.92,English1,,0,0,0,,we have good images of the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.92,0:49:13.12,English1,,0,0,0,,all the way back to its teenage years,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.12,0:49:16.72,English1,,0,0,0,,when large galaxies first formed.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.72,0:49:21.04,English1,,0,0,0,,But before that, we have nothing but a single image -
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.04,0:49:24.96,English1,,0,0,0,,a picture of the universe when it was just 400,000 years old,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.96,0:49:29.56,English1,,0,0,0,,the cosmic microwave background - the afterglow of the big bang.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.56,0:49:32.56,English1,,0,0,0,,It's as though, in the photo album of my life,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.56,0:49:36.20,English1,,0,0,0,,I have nothing before this picture of me aged 16,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.20,0:49:39.52,English1,,0,0,0,,apart from this one of me and my parents in Iraq
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.52,0:49:41.44,English1,,0,0,0,,when I was just a few months old.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.32,0:49:46.20,English1,,0,0,0,,This gap in the childhood of the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.20,0:49:50.08,English1,,0,0,0,,the period between its earliest moments, through the birth
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.08,0:49:54.12,English1,,0,0,0,,of the first stars to the formation of large galaxies
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.12,0:49:57.52,English1,,0,0,0,,is a time known as the dark ages of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.28,0:50:08.64,English1,,0,0,0,,The universe's dark ages lasted for around a billion years
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.64,0:50:12.12,English1,,0,0,0,,and they get their name because there were precious few stars
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.12,0:50:13.72,English1,,0,0,0,,to illuminate them.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.52,0:50:23.28,English1,,0,0,0,,So to fill in those pages in the cosmic photo album, we'd need
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.28,0:50:27.52,English1,,0,0,0,,something capable of seeing where there was next to no light.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.32,0:50:38.80,English1,,0,0,0,,During the Second World War, Bernard Lovell had developed a machine
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.80,0:50:41.08,English1,,0,0,0,,that could see in the dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.08,0:50:43.00,English1,,0,0,0,,He'd worked on airborne radar
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.00,0:50:45.84,English1,,0,0,0,,that mapped bombers' targets on the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.20,0:50:51.28,English1,,0,0,0,,But his real ambition was to build
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.28,0:50:54.00,English1,,0,0,0,,something capable of mapping the heavens.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.76,0:51:30.52,English1,,0,0,0,,The giant dish at Jodrell Bank was Bernard Lovell's baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.52,0:51:34.92,English1,,0,0,0,,It was designed to be the world's largest fully manoeuvrable
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.92,0:51:38.16,English1,,0,0,0,,radio telescope, capable of scouring the entire sky
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.16,0:51:41.52,English1,,0,0,0,,and picking up the longest-wavelength radio signals
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.52,0:51:44.52,English1,,0,0,0,,coming from the deepest recesses of space.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.12,0:52:09.60,English1,,0,0,0,,The Lovell Telescope has a collecting area
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.60,0:52:13.56,English1,,0,0,0,,of 4,560 square metres,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.56,0:52:19.16,English1,,0,0,0,,made up of more than 2,400 galvanised steel plates.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.28,0:52:28.08,English1,,0,0,0,,In the original designs, this bowl of the telescope
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.08,0:52:30.72,English1,,0,0,0,,wasn't meant to be solid like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.72,0:52:34.40,English1,,0,0,0,,The plan was for it to be built of much lighter wire mesh.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.80,0:52:39.76,English1,,0,0,0,,The dish was redesigned
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.76,0:52:44.36,English1,,0,0,0,,because astronomers had discovered a new way of seeing in the dark,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.36,0:52:47.32,English1,,0,0,0,,something that might ultimately allow them
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.32,0:52:50.04,English1,,0,0,0,,to map the universe's dark ages.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.44,0:52:55.80,English1,,0,0,0,,Hydrogen permeates every galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.80,0:52:57.28,English1,,0,0,0,,It was produced in the big bang
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.28,0:53:01.08,English1,,0,0,0,,and is the basic constituent of all normal matter, including us.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.08,0:53:03.36,English1,,0,0,0,,And like most normal matter,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.36,0:53:06.48,English1,,0,0,0,,it wasn't thought to give off any light.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.48,0:53:09.84,English1,,0,0,0,,But then astronomers discovered something remarkable.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.84,0:53:11.88,English1,,0,0,0,,As it floats around in space,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.88,0:53:16.36,English1,,0,0,0,,neutral hydrogen gas is constantly producing radio waves
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.36,0:53:22.84,English1,,0,0,0,,and, crucially, those waves are always the same wavelength - 21cm.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.84,0:53:26.52,English1,,0,0,0,,And this meant that hydrogen could be used to map
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.52,0:53:28.00,English1,,0,0,0,,the galaxies that it fills.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.84,0:53:36.08,English1,,0,0,0,,By detecting the 21cm signal, the Lovell Telescope helped reveal
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.08,0:53:39.84,English1,,0,0,0,,the spiral structure of the Milky Way
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.84,0:53:43.52,English1,,0,0,0,,and produced detailed maps of distant galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.04,0:53:52.20,English1,,0,0,0,,But galaxies aren't the only place in the cosmos you find hydrogen gas.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.20,0:53:54.12,English1,,0,0,0,,During the dark ages of the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.12,0:53:58.08,English1,,0,0,0,,there were no galaxies, but there was plenty of hydrogen.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.08,0:54:03.08,English1,,0,0,0,,So by detecting the 21cm signal from these primordial gas clouds,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.08,0:54:05.68,English1,,0,0,0,,you could see the universe in its infancy
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.68,0:54:08.48,English1,,0,0,0,,and peer into the dark ages themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.12,0:54:18.96,English1,,0,0,0,,And by doing so, we'll be able to watch dark matter
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.96,0:54:20.88,English1,,0,0,0,,pull the cosmos together...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.80,0:54:24.68,English1,,0,0,0,,..and light up the heavens.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.12,0:54:31.32,English1,,0,0,0,,It was during the dark ages that the hydrogen gas created
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.32,0:54:36.36,English1,,0,0,0,,in the big bang was compressed into stars and moulded into galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.36,0:54:41.12,English1,,0,0,0,,It was in this era that the cosmos as we know it was born,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.12,0:54:44.76,English1,,0,0,0,,sculpted by the gravitational pull of dark matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.20,0:54:55.00,English1,,0,0,0,,But the machine scientists are building to map the dark ages
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.00,0:54:57.20,English1,,0,0,0,,will see far more.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.64,0:55:03.24,English1,,0,0,0,,With an effective collecting area of more than 200 times that
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.24,0:55:07.16,English1,,0,0,0,,of the Lovell Telescope, the square kilometre array
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.16,0:55:10.76,English1,,0,0,0,,will be capable of mapping a billion galaxies,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.76,0:55:15.08,English1,,0,0,0,,tracking the expansion and evolution of the entire universe
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.08,0:55:17.20,English1,,0,0,0,,more accurately than ever before.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.96,0:55:25.36,English1,,0,0,0,,And the hope is, that by doing so,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.36,0:55:29.00,English1,,0,0,0,,it will provide clues to the nature of dark energy
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.00,0:55:31.64,English1,,0,0,0,,and the universe's ultimate fate.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.40,0:55:56.48,English1,,0,0,0,,Using hydrogen to map the cosmos might just represent the final
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.48,0:56:02.08,English1,,0,0,0,,chapter of humankind's exploration of the universe using light,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.08,0:56:07.28,English1,,0,0,0,,a journey that began in earnest some 400 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.28,0:56:12.28,English1,,0,0,0,,In December 1609, Galileo Galilei began making observations
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.28,0:56:14.28,English1,,0,0,0,,of the night sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.28,0:56:17.40,English1,,0,0,0,,Before then, what was thought to be out there was essentially
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.40,0:56:19.20,English1,,0,0,0,,a matter of faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.20,0:56:23.00,English1,,0,0,0,,The universe at large lay unseen and unseeable.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.00,0:56:24.72,English1,,0,0,0,,But now, for the first time,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.72,0:56:27.88,English1,,0,0,0,,the nature of the heavens was something knowable -
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.88,0:56:31.04,English1,,0,0,0,,you simply had to look up and see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.04,0:56:34.24,English1,,0,0,0,,The light captured in Galileo's simple telescope
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.24,0:56:37.56,English1,,0,0,0,,began a chain of discoveries that would reveal
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.56,0:56:39.76,English1,,0,0,0,,the true nature of the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.24,0:56:49.48,English1,,0,0,0,,We've seen galaxies
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.48,0:56:52.52,English1,,0,0,0,,billions of light years' distance from the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.00,0:56:58.36,English1,,0,0,0,,And as we've come to understand light's properties,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.36,0:57:01.52,English1,,0,0,0,,we've discovered the stuff of which stars are made...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.28,0:57:08.64,English1,,0,0,0,,..and glimpsed the beginning of the universe itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.80,0:57:21.60,English1,,0,0,0,,But the realisation that most normal matter can't be seen
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.60,0:57:26.64,English1,,0,0,0,,and the discovery of dark matter and dark energy
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.64,0:57:32.40,English1,,0,0,0,,mean that more than 99% of the universe lies hidden in the shadows.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.40,0:57:40.32,English1,,0,0,0,,And as dark energy pushes the galaxies ever further apart,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.32,0:57:43.72,English1,,0,0,0,,what few lights there are will begin to go out.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.40,0:57:48.24,English1,,0,0,0,,As the universe expands ever faster,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.24,0:57:52.72,English1,,0,0,0,,one by one the galaxies will disappear from view.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.72,0:57:57.12,English1,,0,0,0,,All that will remain visible will be the stars in our own galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.12,0:58:00.44,English1,,0,0,0,,It would be almost as if we'd never invented the telescope at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.84,0:58:04.64,English1,,0,0,0,,For the vast majority of the universe's life,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.64,0:58:08.36,English1,,0,0,0,,there'll be no way of discovering all the things we have about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.12,0:58:14.16,English1,,0,0,0,,So I don't feel disheartened that so much of the cosmos
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.16,0:58:16.40,English1,,0,0,0,,is hidden in the shadows.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.40,0:58:17.56,English1,,0,0,0,,The real miracle is
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.56,0:58:20.80,English1,,0,0,0,,that when we first looked out into the depths of space
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.80,0:58:23.48,English1,,0,0,0,,there was any light to see at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.84,0:58:36.44,English1,,0,0,0,,Whether you want to step into the light
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.44,0:58:38.96,English1,,0,0,0,,or explore the mysteries of the dark,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.96,0:58:41.52,English1,,0,0,0,,let the Open University inspire you.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.52,0:58:42.84,English1,,0,0,0,,Go to...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.40,0:58:48.20,English1,,0,0,0,,..and follow links to The Open University.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.20,0:58:51.28,English1,,0,0,0,,Subtitles by Red Bee Media Ltd
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.84,0:00:19.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当太阳落下地平线时
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.84,0:00:22.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它的光芒开始黯淡下来
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.64,0:00:27.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,夜幕降临，我们的世界沉浸在黑暗之中
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.96,0:00:46.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,今天，在灯火辉煌的小镇和城市
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.36,0:00:49.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们几乎体验不到真正的黑暗
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.60,0:00:52.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是，没有我们双眼的引导
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.24,0:00:55.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,世界会变得更加神秘
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.32,0:01:14.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我现在什么也看不见
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.16,0:01:17.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但很奇怪，我依然能感觉到树的存在
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.64,0:01:19.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们将我包裹在夜色中
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.96,0:01:24.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我看不到它们，但我知道有东西就在那里
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.60,0:01:35.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,同样，当我们探索宇宙时
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.84,0:01:38.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们已经意识到，对外太空有些什么
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.20,0:01:40.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们只能看到仅有的线索
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.20,0:01:48.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们最好的估计是，超过99%的宇宙
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.00,0:01:52.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,隐藏于黑暗之中，我们的望远镜看不到
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.72,0:01:54.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也超越了我们的理解范围
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.28,0:02:00.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,本片故事讲述的就是，我们本以为
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.84,0:02:04.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们已经接近于完全理解宇宙，
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.40,0:02:08.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,后来却意识到，我们所看到只是宇宙的零头
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.84,0:02:12.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后进行了非凡的探索，来揭开在宇宙的黑暗深处
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.92,0:02:14.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,究竟有什么
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.92,0:02:21.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这几乎是最重要的科学事业
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.80,0:02:25.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为我们的宇宙隐藏于黑暗中
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.84,0:02:29.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,黑暗总有一天会撕裂它
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.40,0:02:53.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,几个世纪以来，科学家用光构建了一张
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.84,0:02:56.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,似乎是全方位的宇宙图像
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.20,0:03:01.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们已经发现，地球只是一颗行星
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.00,0:03:02.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它的轨道绕着太阳
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.88,0:03:06.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而太阳自己是一颗恒星
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.48,0:03:09.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,组成它的物质与其他无数的星星一样
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.52,0:03:14.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这些星星照亮了浩瀚的，有可能是无尽的，宇宙
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.08,0:03:29.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是有一个小问题却400多年
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.56,0:03:32.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,都没有解决，问题是这样的
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.72,0:03:34.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,天空中有这么多星星
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.48,0:03:36.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,为什么那里是完全黑暗的？
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.76,0:03:42.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,关于黑暗的故事，就开始于这个简单的问题
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.00,0:03:47.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,其核心部分就是一个深刻的佯谬
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.64,0:03:53.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在森林中，无论我把手电筒指向哪个方向
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.32,0:03:56.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,光柱总是会遇到树干
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.80,0:04:00.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,正像我无论看哪里都能看到一棵树一样
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.88,0:04:03.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果宇宙足够大
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.44,0:04:08.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那么，从地球看出去每一条视线都会碰到一颗星
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.36,0:04:10.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,夜晚的天空就完全不应该是黑的
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.96,0:04:13.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它应该是星光闪耀的
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.40,0:04:19.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个问题在1570年代第一次提出
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.20,0:04:23.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就是后来众所周知的奥伯斯佯谬
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.92,0:04:29.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一个可能的解释是，地球
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.84,0:04:34.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,被不发光物质所包围，使我们看不到后面的星星
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.80,0:04:39.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是不久人们就意识到，这些不发光的云雾会
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.16,0:04:43.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,吸收星光的能量，变热，最终
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.28,0:04:46.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,会发光，与被它们阻挡的星体一样明亮
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.60,0:04:57.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个佯谬在20世纪才有一个满意的解释
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.00,0:05:03.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,答案是 - 夜晚的天空变黑的理由是
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.16,0:05:06.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,宇宙有一个开始
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.64,0:05:11.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,宇宙开始于138亿年前的大爆炸，所以
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.28,0:05:13.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们只会看到这样的星星，
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.58,0:05:16.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们的光线抵达我们这里需要时间
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.28,0:05:19.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,天空是黑的，就是因为最远的那些星星的光
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.88,0:05:21.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,还没有到达我们地球
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.96,0:05:34.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,并没有什么神秘的物质阻碍星光
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.32,0:05:38.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,还在抵达地球的路上的星光，所穿越的黑暗空间就是空的
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.24,0:05:41.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,宇宙学家在夜晚可以安然入睡了
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.52,0:05:46.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是不久之后，我们开始看到一些线索显示
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.64,0:05:49.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,除了我们眼睛看到的，太空中还有别的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.20,0:05:52.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也就是说，空荡空间的阴暗角落
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.56,0:05:55.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,可能终究不是空空荡荡的
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.24,0:06:00.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,事实上第一个线索的显现
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.84,0:06:04.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是在大约200年前
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.16,0:06:07.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不是在宇宙的深处，就在我们地球的后院
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.04,0:06:23.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,17世纪望远镜的发明，让我们能够
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.32,0:06:27.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,看到太阳系最深区域发出来的微弱光线
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.92,0:06:34.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在1781年，望远镜找到了第七颗行星，天王星
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.40,0:06:37.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是古人没有见到过的
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.96,0:06:42.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是，这个新的行星有些奇怪
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.16,0:06:46.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,天文学家发现，随着时间的流逝，天王星的准确位置
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.72,0:06:50.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,越来越偏离引力定律
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.08,0:06:53.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所预测的位置
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.20,0:06:57.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一种解释是，定律本身是错的
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.08,0:06:59.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是，有一个在巴黎天文台工作的人
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.20,0:07:02.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,提出了一个不同的解决方案
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.08,0:07:04.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那里还有别的物体
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.08,0:07:08.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就是我们看不到的这个物体，干扰了天王星的轨道
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.28,0:07:23.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,1846年，数学家奥本·勒维耶
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.52,0:07:28.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,受雇于天文台来计算彗星
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.32,0:07:30.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,穿越太阳系时的轨道
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.32,0:07:36.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,并预测它们何时点亮夜空
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.56,0:07:43.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,人们这样描述勒维耶，说他有一种几乎病态的
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.96,0:07:48.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,需求，强迫他身边的每样东西和每个人保持有序
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.28,0:07:51.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不能容忍人们犯错和软弱
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.48,0:07:56.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当被问到他是什么样子时，一个同事说
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.04,0:07:58.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我不知道勒维耶先生实际上
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.72,0:08:01.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是否是法国最讨厌的人
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.04,0:08:04.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但我十分肯定他是最讨厌的
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.28,0:08:09.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但他无疑是一个数学天才
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.04,0:08:11.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他对别人很苛刻，对自己也一样
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.04,0:08:17.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为他是一个数学家，他着手寻找
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.88,0:08:22.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他认为正在影响天王星的新天体
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.40,0:08:27.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不是用望远镜梳理天空，而是通过计算来确定它的位置
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.32,0:08:41.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这些就是勒维耶1846年的原始手稿本
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.20,0:08:42.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这本叫做
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.36,0:08:45.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“寻找干扰物体. 二阶近似.”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.08,0:08:52.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它包括了一页又一页
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.48,0:08:55.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,复杂的数学计算
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.88,0:09:08.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,勒维耶所尝试的做法完全不同于
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.44,0:09:10.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,天文学中的常规做法
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.64,0:09:12.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也就是你知道一个天体在哪里 -
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.84,0:09:17.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,比如一颗恒星或行星或彗星 - 然后利用引力定律
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.80,0:09:22.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,来解释它对附近天体的影响
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.04,0:09:25.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而在这里，他不知道他那个干扰天体在哪里
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.28,0:09:30.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他计算的唯一依靠就是它对天王星的轨道的影响
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.04,0:09:34.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以他先对干扰天体的位置做出某些初始假定
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.20,0:09:39.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后进行计算，预测它对天王星产生的影响
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.08,0:09:42.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后与观察结果相比较
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.08,0:09:45.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当二者不匹配时，他再回头调整
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.68,0:09:48.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他最初的假定，然后再重新计算一遍
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.76,0:09:53.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他就这样一次又一次重复
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.04,0:09:55.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,直到预测与观察相匹配时才停下来
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.12,0:10:04.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,1846年8月31号
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.56,0:10:07.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在艰苦工作三个月后
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.60,0:10:11.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,勒维耶把他的结果提交给法国科学院
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.08,0:10:13.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他宣布，他的计算显示
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.80,0:10:16.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他相信是一颗新行星
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.72,0:10:20.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,最关键的是，他给出了夜晚天空的坐标
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.32,0:10:22.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,用于找到那个新行星
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.16,0:10:30.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然而，尽管如此，他还是不能说服
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.36,0:10:33.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,任何法国天文学家去找到他所说的行星
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.12,0:10:41.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,最后，勒维耶把他的计算结果
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.20,0:10:44.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,寄给了柏林天文台的约翰·加勒
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.48,0:10:47.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他的信于9月23日寄到
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.80,0:10:50.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,同一天晚上，他就找到了那颗新行星
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.76,0:10:54.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它的位置与勒维耶预测的地方差距在一度以内
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.80,0:10:57.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他的计算如此精确
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.56,0:11:00.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,以至于加勒找到这颗行星只用了不到一个钟头
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.04,0:11:11.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,勒维耶和加勒发现了海王星
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.96,0:11:17.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一个巨大的冰球，是地球重量的17倍
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.44,0:11:20.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,体积是地球的60倍
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.00,0:11:24.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,潜伏在离太阳大约40亿千米的阴影中
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.92,0:11:33.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,海王星很难被发现
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.04,0:11:36.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不是因为它的内部有什么神秘物质
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.24,0:11:40.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,只是因为黑暗，因为它离太阳太远了
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.08,0:11:42.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,只有极珍贵的一点阳光照亮它
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.56,0:11:46.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而在我们的太阳系之外
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.76,0:11:50.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,缺乏照明就成了一个更大的问题
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.16,0:11:56.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这也意味着有更多物质隐藏在黑暗中
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.28,0:12:04.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,人们认为恒星只包含了宇宙中11%的原子
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.08,0:12:08.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,剩下的 - 气体云和粉尘，行星，已死亡的恒星 -
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.72,0:12:12.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们都看不见，因为它们几乎不发任何光
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.28,0:12:17.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,恒星之间的黑暗空间并不完全是空的
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.40,0:12:20.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,事实上，绝大多数物质
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.16,0:12:22.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,都包含在这黑暗空间中
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.84,0:12:30.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,到20世纪中叶，大多数天文学家相信
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.92,0:12:36.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,虽然有近90%的物质我们看不到
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.00,0:12:39.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,整个宇宙依然是完全可见的
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.44,0:12:40.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,至少理论上是如此
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.68,0:12:45.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但这种观点就要改变了
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.16,0:12:51.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,欢迎来到白沙导弹试验场
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.92,0:13:03.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在1964年，NASA的科学家们在一个空蜂火箭
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.76,0:13:06.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,安装了一台X射线探测器
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.00,0:13:07.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,...二，一...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.96,0:13:12.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,将它发射到大气空间边缘
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.28,0:13:18.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在大气层的X射线吸收层之外
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.72,0:13:21.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,探测器检测到某种极其明显的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.72,0:13:24.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,位于天鹅座
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.80,0:13:32.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,年轻的英国天文学家保罗·马丁被这个
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.52,0:13:36.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,神秘的X射线源迷住了，这个源被命名为 天鹅座X-1
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.08,0:13:38.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在他加入格林威治天文台的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.48,0:13:40.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也就是1971年夏天
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.36,0:13:43.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他得到了一个绝好的机会去发现它(天鹅座X-1)是什么
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.56,0:13:48.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,大家知道在将气体加热到
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.16,0:13:53.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一百万度以上的时候就会产生X射线
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.04,0:13:54.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,【门铃响了】
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.80,0:13:56.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,嗨，保罗！
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.56,0:14:00.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是没有人确切知道，在外太空中
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.20,0:14:02.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,有什么能导致这种极端条件存在
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.76,0:14:06.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,关于X射线源是什么让你觉得有趣？
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.76,0:14:10.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那是天体的X射线源刚刚被发现
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.08,0:14:13.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,太空中的X射线来自于好几个地方
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.12,0:14:14.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是一种能量很高的辐射
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.72,0:14:17.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这意味着有某种威力巨大的事情在那里发生
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.60,0:14:21.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我的意思是，X射线是一种标志，表示恒星正在向你招手
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.12,0:14:24.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,说，“看看我，看看我，看看我 - 瞧我多有趣.”
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.04,0:14:30.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但当保罗把他的光学望远镜调整到那个源的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.64,0:14:34.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他看到的只是一颗常见的普通恒星
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.24,0:14:37.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它附近也没有哪里是热到能产生X射线的
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.00,0:14:42.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,大多数恒星都构成一个体系，有两颗星的
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.52,0:14:45.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,三颗星的，甚至有五颗星或者更多的
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.04,0:14:49.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,像太阳这样自己构成一个体系的情况并不常见
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.24,0:14:51.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因此我决定试试
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.32,0:14:54.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,从这可能看见的恒星上寻找证据
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.72,0:14:58.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,看看附近是否有另一颗星，它们相互绕着对方旋转
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.44,0:15:02.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这样一夜一夜地记录它的运动，保罗发现
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.32,0:15:08.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这颗星的轨道绕着一颗不可见的伙伴，每5.6天绕一周
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.36,0:15:12.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一旦你知道一颗双子星的周期，你就能计算
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.92,0:15:18.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,双子星系统和它的各个子星的质量
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.44,0:15:20.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以，这就是接下来要做的事情
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.44,0:15:23.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后，可能就在一个钟头内
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.08,0:15:27.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我就知道了这颗我看不见的星
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.76,0:15:31.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是太阳质量的四倍或更多
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.80,0:15:37.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这样重的东西离那颗看得见的恒星这样近
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.64,0:15:40.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就会从它的外层剥去它的物质，
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.88,0:15:46.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,巨大的摩檫力就会将气体加热到能产生X射线的程度
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.60,0:15:54.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是物理学家只知道有一种物体会
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.12,0:15:57.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如此之大却依然完全看不见
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.28,0:16:00.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这种物体只是在理论上存在着
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.80,0:16:05.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,保罗·马丁发现了第一个黑洞
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.16,0:16:12.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我简直是...我简直是高兴坏了
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.88,0:16:17.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我不得不离开书桌，来回走动一下，以便平静下来
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.20,0:16:19.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我的脉搏也加快了
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.00,0:16:23.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我知道这太重大了，所以我也有点害怕出错
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.12,0:16:24.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以我知道我应该再非常仔细地检查一下
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.88,0:16:30.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,又重新做一遍，检查一下我做的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.08,0:16:31.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是这是...这真是一个伟大的时刻
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.80,0:16:35.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那天余下的时间里，我无法平静下来做任何正经事
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.12,0:16:39.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我感到...我真为自己感到高兴，真的
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.72,0:16:45.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,多亏了保罗·马丁
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.36,0:16:50.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,宇宙现在有了一种极度黑暗的新居民
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.28,0:16:55.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,黑洞的密度令人难以置信
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.92,0:17:00.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们的引力把它们周围的空间和时间弯曲到如此程度，
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.16,0:17:05.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,以至于无论什么东西，甚至光，都无法逃离它
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.08,0:17:15.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当你接近一个黑洞时
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.00,0:17:17.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一个在远处看着你的观察者
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.20,0:17:21.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,会看到从你身上发出的光变得越来越红
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.52,0:17:24.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而且看到你运动的很慢
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.60,0:17:28.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为黑洞强大的引力
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.40,0:17:31.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,既扭曲了空间也扭曲了时间
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.76,0:17:35.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后，当你穿过了视界之后
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.52,0:17:39.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也就是没有回头路的那个点，那是黑洞的边缘
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.44,0:17:44.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你就消失了，从宇宙永远被抹去了
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.76,0:17:58.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,无论你把多少光照向它们
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.20,0:18:01.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,黑洞依然是黑的
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.12,0:18:07.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,观察它们对其他物体的影响
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.12,0:18:10.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们已经在银河系发现了几十个黑洞
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.96,0:18:14.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而人们估计整个宇宙中
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.04,0:18:16.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一定有数十亿个黑洞
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.16,0:18:19.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,巨大，特大质量的黑洞
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.44,0:18:22.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,质量为太阳的数百万倍
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.20,0:18:25.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,位于几乎每一个星系的心脏部位
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.40,0:18:36.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,哪怕像黑洞一样奇怪
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.52,0:18:40.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,毕竟是我们期望能够找到的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.12,0:18:44.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们的理论已经预测到它们的存在
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.88,0:18:46.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,并描述了它们的性质
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.96,0:18:51.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是自20世纪30年代以来
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.92,0:18:56.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,天文学家已经看到了令人不安的线索，提示有比黑洞更奇怪的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.84,0:19:04.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这种物质是完全不可见的，也完全在预料之外
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.40,0:19:10.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,『低语声』
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.12,0:19:18.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,还是一个孩子的时候，薇拉·鲁宾经常数小时深夜醒来
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.52,0:19:21.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,看着她床头的窗户外面
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.32,0:19:24.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,凝望着星星划过天空
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.68,0:19:31.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,后来，在她30多岁的时候已是为人之母
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.56,0:19:34.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,她决定去实现她的童年梦想
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.48,0:19:37.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,把天文学家作为自己的职业
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.52,0:19:39.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,『低语声』
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.60,0:19:52.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在20世纪六十年代，天文学中最热门的课题就是类星体
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.88,0:19:57.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是因为野外嘈杂
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.52,0:20:01.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,研究类星体所必须的最大的望远镜
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.24,0:20:03.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,经常在地球最偏远的地方
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.76,0:20:08.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,研究类星体就意味着要在离家很远的地方工作很长时间
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.32,0:20:10.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以薇拉必须找到一个研究课题
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.76,0:20:14.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不影响她做上班族妈妈
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.08,0:20:17.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,同时，这个领域还必须比较小，以便她能够真正达到目的
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.00,0:20:29.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就这样，她开始一个项目，测量恒星在星系中的移动方式
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.04,0:20:31.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这些星系就像我们自己的银河系
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.80,0:20:59.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,— 哇!『— 他笑了』
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.88,0:21:10.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,星系中的所有物体都在移动和旋转
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.24,0:21:13.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一分钟内，地球会绕太阳
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.04,0:21:16.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,旅行近2000千米
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.16,0:21:23.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而在同样的时间内，太阳和整个太阳系
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.04,0:21:28.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,会绕着银河系中心旅行1万2000千米
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.60,0:21:33.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,哇
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.88,0:21:35.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我可不喜欢这样！
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.08,0:21:45.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果你认为这转得快，那么考虑一下这个
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.56,0:21:50.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,地球绕太阳飞行速度是每小时10万8000千米
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.04,0:21:55.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,哈！太阳和整个太阳系
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.24,0:21:59.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,绕银河系中心飞行的速度是
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.08,0:22:01.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,每小时72万千米
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.52,0:22:03.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,『他笑了』
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.44,0:22:09.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我现在可以停下来了吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.08,0:22:22.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这可要了我的命，真的
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.48,0:22:24.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,太感谢了
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.04,0:22:33.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是当薇拉·鲁宾测量仙女座星系里
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.16,0:22:35.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,绕星系中心轨道运行的恒星速度时
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.68,0:22:38.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,她发现了令人深感困惑的事情
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.64,0:22:45.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果我画一幅图，纵轴表示
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.28,0:22:48.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们太阳系中的行星的速度
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.44,0:22:51.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,横轴表示它们到太阳的距离
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.36,0:22:57.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我发现，离太阳最近的行星，水星，轨道速度最快
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.16,0:23:03.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后是金星，地球，火星，等等
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.32,0:23:07.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,离太阳越远
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.52,0:23:09.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,轨道速度越慢
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.52,0:23:13.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,事实上，海王星与其他行星比起来移动的很慢
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.56,0:23:16.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它的轨道离太阳如此之远
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.36,0:23:19.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,以至于从我们在167年前发现它以来
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.08,0:23:21.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,只绕轨道运行了一整圈
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.16,0:23:28.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,现在，如果我再画一张同样的速度-距离图
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.52,0:23:31.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是这一次，速度是
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.12,0:23:34.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,恒星绕星系中心轨道运行的速度
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.64,0:23:36.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,距离则是恒星到星系中心的距离
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.56,0:23:39.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我希望看到，对于更外面的恒星
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.28,0:23:43.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,速度随着距离而下降，就像太阳系的行星一样
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.20,0:23:46.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是当薇拉·鲁宾做出她的数据图形时
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.64,0:23:49.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,她发现你越往外面更远
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.12,0:23:52.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,恒星的速度并不是越慢下来
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.28,0:23:54.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而是大致维持不变
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.84,0:23:59.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,行星月往外面更远运动的越慢
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.84,0:24:01.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为当你走得越远
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.68,0:24:04.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,太阳的引力场就会变得越微弱
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.96,0:24:10.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以，任何移动得太快的物体就会干脆飞向外太空
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.32,0:24:13.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是薇拉·鲁宾从星系得到的结果
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.04,0:24:15.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,暗示一定有一个额外的引力源
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.96,0:24:19.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,让这些快速移动的星体保持在它们的轨道上
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.44,0:24:25.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这种额外的引力是必须的
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.40,0:24:29.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为天文学家把包括他们能想到的
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.08,0:24:33.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所有可能潜伏在星系中的黑暗物质
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.20,0:24:37.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,行星，尘埃云，甚至黑洞的引力都加起来
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.00,0:24:40.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,要导致星体的速度
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.24,0:24:42.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,像薇拉·鲁宾所测得的那样
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.16,0:24:44.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,其引力依然少大约10倍
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.76,0:24:49.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,有两个可能的解释
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.00,0:24:52.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,要么爱因斯坦的引力理论是错的
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.36,0:24:56.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,要么星系被一种全新的物质所充满
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.48,0:24:58.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这种东西不是由原子构成
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.36,0:25:01.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,完全不可见，而且非常重
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.68,0:25:03.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是一种新的黑暗物质形式
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.84,0:25:06.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,天文学家命名这种东西为... 暗物质
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.24,0:25:23.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,毫不奇怪，比起接受
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.80,0:25:28.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,星系中充满了某种神秘的看不见的物质
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.08,0:25:31.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一些物理学家再次想到，修改引力定律
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.88,0:25:33.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,可能是最简单的解决方案
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.68,0:25:40.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,直到天文学家捕获了一副惊人的画面
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.60,0:25:43.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,对我而言，这是现代天文学中
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.28,0:25:45.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,最令我吃惊的画面之一
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.64,0:25:50.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是一张星系簇团的照片，名叫“子弹星系团”
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.96,0:25:54.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它的这个名称来源于这种子弹形状的气体云，
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.12,0:25:58.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它实际上是由碰撞引起的冲击波
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.96,0:26:03.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不只是气体云或恒星，甚至也不是整个星系
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.48,0:26:06.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而是星系团簇相遇后
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.80,0:26:11.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,相互穿过，速度达每小时1000万千米
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.48,0:26:18.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当我想到这碰撞规模之巨大时，都感到一阵眩晕
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.12,0:26:23.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是碰撞规模的巨大
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.56,0:26:26.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,并不会使这幅照片如此重要
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.00,0:26:29.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是碰撞对簇团的各部分产生的后果使它变得重要
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.84,0:26:33.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当这些星系团相遇时
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.12,0:26:35.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,星系中的恒星和行星
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.12,0:26:37.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,大部分会相互穿过
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.04,0:26:40.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为虽然它们很大，但它们之间的距离也很大
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.88,0:26:45.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,两颗恒星相撞的机会事实上很小
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.36,0:26:48.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是那些尘埃和气体就不是这样了
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.12,0:26:53.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们的质量占我们能看见的星系总物质的90%
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.40,0:26:57.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当它们碰撞时，它们就产生了巨大的热云
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.24,0:27:00.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也就是位于照片中心的两块粉红色区域
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.60,0:27:05.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是，如果大多数质量都陷于云的这里，
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.16,0:27:09.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那么你一定希望大多数引力也会以那里为中心
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.08,0:27:11.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是你所看到的并不是这样
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.04,0:27:15.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这些更外面的蓝色区域表明光在这里被弯曲
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.72,0:27:19.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为引力把空间自身的构造扭曲了
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.80,0:27:23.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这就意味着大多数引力的中心在这里
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.44,0:27:25.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而不是在正中间
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.60,0:27:28.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,对此，最简单的解释是
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.28,0:27:30.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在星系团相互撞击的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.80,0:27:33.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,并不只有恒星和行星相互穿过
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.64,0:27:35.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,还有其他物质穿过
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.36,0:27:38.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这种物质巨大，但不可见
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.28,0:27:41.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这幅图片是我们未曾有过的
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.92,0:27:43.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,证明暗物质存在的最好证据
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.48,0:27:55.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,现在人们普遍接受了暗物质是真实的观点
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.08,0:27:59.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这意味着宇宙中的物质比我们曾经设想过的多很多
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.00,0:28:02.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,事实上，暗物质的数量
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.96,0:28:06.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是正常物质的四倍之多
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.84,0:28:13.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,宇宙中如此之多的东西，不光是看不见
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.64,0:28:16.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们从本质上来说就是不可见的
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.08,0:28:20.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,暗物质如此难以捉摸的原因是
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.12,0:28:24.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它既不反射光也不发射光
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.60,0:28:27.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以我们就看不见它
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.24,0:28:31.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,还有比这更糟糕的，正常的物质之所以具有固体性
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.04,0:28:33.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是因为有电磁力
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.56,0:28:36.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而暗物质粒子感受不到这种力
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.68,0:28:39.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以它们就会直接穿过其它物质
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.32,0:28:43.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们能有的唯一希望就是它们是否能和原子核迎头相撞
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.56,0:28:47.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而且即使它们撞上了，我们也极难探测到这种撞击
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.72,0:28:54.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以，对暗物质的搜寻
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.20,0:28:59.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,已经从极大的方面转到极小的方面
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.80,0:29:07.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,从用望远镜梳理天空
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.36,0:29:10.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,转到把探测器深埋于地下
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.56,0:29:13.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在寻找暗物质的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.80,0:29:17.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我正在前往的地方，几乎相当于宇宙的中心
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.56,0:29:27.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这就是格兰萨索国家实验室
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.00,0:29:31.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,位于几乎1500米岩石覆盖的地下
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.16,0:29:36.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,要到达那里，只能通过一条
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.44,0:29:39.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,深入到意大利亚平宁山脉的隧道
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.24,0:29:47.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,之所以把实验室建在一座山里面
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.60,0:29:52.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是因为地球总是持续地受到宇宙射线的轰击
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.52,0:29:54.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们与外层大气发生碰撞
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.96,0:29:57.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,产生级联放大的粒子流
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.24,0:30:00.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,倾泻到地球表面
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.16,0:30:05.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我头顶上的岩石形成了一个有效的1400米厚的顶层
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.72,0:30:08.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,吸收掉绝大部分这些粒子
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.72,0:30:12.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,屏蔽和保护下面的设备
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.20,0:30:14.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是，对暗物质搜寻者而言，最关键的是
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.92,0:30:17.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,暗物质直接穿过正常物质
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.16,0:30:18.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,直接穿过岩石
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.48,0:30:20.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,并希望它进入到他们的探测器
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.16,0:30:28.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,哇！
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.36,0:30:30.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这看起来像邦德的邪恶巢穴
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.12,0:31:03.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,格兰萨索是世界上最大的地下实验室
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.60,0:31:11.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在过去十年里
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.36,0:31:15.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它就是暗物质科学家的家，比如Chamkaur Ghag博士
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.36,0:31:18.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他在DarkSide-50探测器上工作
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.12,0:31:21.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,其上进行的是五个暗物质实验之一
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.92,0:31:34.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,- 这是发网.  - 发网.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.20,0:31:36.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,或者叫头网, 我头发少.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.60,0:31:43.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,毫克水平的粉尘就能毁坏实验. - 好的
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.96,0:32:02.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,看起来非常让人印象深刻
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.16,0:32:03.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,- 是哦. - 相当科幻啊.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.68,0:32:10.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那么给我讲讲，这个实验怎样运转啊？
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.96,0:32:13.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,好的，整个实验搭建起来就像一个俄罗斯玩偶
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.68,0:32:16.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,最外面的一层就是这座高山自身
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.36,0:32:19.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,用来保护实验免受太空辐射的影响
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.96,0:32:22.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后就是这个水槽，就是我们站着的地方
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.52,0:32:25.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个水槽会被水完全淹没
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.12,0:32:27.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,什么，整个缸都淹？
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.12,0:32:29.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,绝对正确。全部放满，直到这个边沿
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.84,0:32:33.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,大约有750立方米的水会放到这里面
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.08,0:32:37.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就是要阻止来自实验室和我们周围的岩石的辐射
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.04,0:32:40.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这保护着这个巨大的金属球，就是这，
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.36,0:32:42.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它是最后一层保护层
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.16,0:32:45.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后就是DarkSide装置本身了，就在这里面
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.32,0:32:47.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这就是探测器，这个实验的心脏
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.76,0:32:50.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就是这个东西，将会探测暗物质
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.20,0:32:55.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,- 这里没有一个灯的开关咧.   - 嗯，没有.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.20,0:32:57.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我要爬到那里看一看
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.36,0:33:06.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,DarkSide-50是设计用来探测
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.84,0:33:09.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一类新的基本粒子的
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.44,0:33:12.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,叫做大质量弱相互作用粒子（WIMP）
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.04,0:33:17.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,根据理论预测，人们认为这些WIMP
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.72,0:33:21.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,可能就是组成暗物质的材料
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.28,0:33:27.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那么在中间的那个金属球，那就是DarkSide吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.68,0:33:30.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,对. 这是一个探测器，装满了150千克的液态氩
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.80,0:33:32.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,暗物质粒子应该
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.44,0:33:34.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一直都在流过这个探测器
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.76,0:33:36.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是绝大多数都只是直接穿过
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.88,0:33:39.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为它们是非常弱的相互作用粒子
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.44,0:33:42.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果我们运气好，就会遇到一个粒子撞上某个氩原子的核
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.80,0:33:45.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就会发生闪光，探测器就会捕捉到
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.32,0:33:54.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,DarkSide还没有开始搜索
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.24,0:33:57.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是在实验室隧道迷宫的其他地方
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.16,0:34:00.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们已经看到了诱人的提示
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.00,0:34:05.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是已经开始运行的XENON100实验
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.60,0:34:07.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,正在获取数据，已经有一段时间了
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.44,0:34:11.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它是当今世界最敏感的暗物质探测器
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.04,0:34:15.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是一个暗物质数据获取的实况
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.00,0:34:18.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那么，确切地说... 你们正在寻找的是哪种信号或形状?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.44,0:34:21.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,哦，我们正在寻找一种初始闪光
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.48,0:34:23.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那会是一种非常尖的尖峰，就像这样，
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.32,0:34:26.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后是一个更大的峰，像那个一样，
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.88,0:34:30.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它就是在液态氙顶部的
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.12,0:34:32.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,气体层生成的光
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.12,0:34:34.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,哦. 事实上, 这可能也是一个不错的信号
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.56,0:34:35.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这边请.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.80,0:34:38.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那么那些事件，那些峰值的任何一个
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.08,0:34:39.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,都可能是一个暗物质粒子？
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.96,0:34:42.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,正是. 任何一个这样的事件
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.48,0:34:45.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,都有可能是在XENON100中
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.40,0:34:46.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,发生相互作用的暗物质
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.84,0:34:49.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,只是在分析这些数据之前，我们还不能确定
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.68,0:34:53.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为它太敏感了
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.72,0:34:56.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,绝大多数这些峰值
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.56,0:34:59.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,都是因为组成探测器本身的
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.40,0:35:01.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,金属所发出来的辐射
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.76,0:35:09.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是我们希望像这样的实验
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.32,0:35:12.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在未来十年内一定能
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.60,0:35:14.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,探测到暗物质粒子
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.76,0:35:25.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,今天，我们认为暗物质不光存在，
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.12,0:35:28.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而且是我们宇宙至关重要的一部分
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.40,0:35:32.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为没有它，我们能看到的世界将不会存在
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.80,0:35:36.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为暗物质不仅把星系维持在一起
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.80,0:35:41.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而且正是它把尘埃云集合到一起
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.16,0:35:46.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,形成星系，从而使恒星能够在其中点火燃烧起来
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.48,0:35:57.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,暗物质最初只是一种奇怪的巧合
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.44,0:36:01.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,使恒星绕星系边缘按特定方式运动
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.04,0:36:04.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,现在它成了恒星和星系存在的理由
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.52,0:36:14.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是在20世纪90年代末期，在科学家试图
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.36,0:36:17.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,到底有多少暗物质的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.56,0:36:20.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,又有了一个令人惊讶的发现
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.16,0:36:23.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,还有某种更神秘的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.28,0:36:25.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,更难以捉摸的东西存在于太空
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.32,0:36:29.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,为了搞清楚那到底是什么
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.40,0:36:34.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你要回到万物诞生之初
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.00,0:36:36.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,宇宙开始于一个巨大的火球
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.40,0:36:49.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,138亿年前，宇宙诞生了
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.00,0:36:51.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在这被称为大爆炸的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.52,0:36:54.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,万物同时被创造出来
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.24,0:36:58.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,看到了这巨大的闪光吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.92,0:37:02.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那就是所有原子碎片正结合在一起形成气团
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.84,0:37:05.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,现在气团在形成块状物体
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.28,0:37:07.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后形成巨大的恒星星系
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.20,0:37:14.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们现在所看到的宇宙的膨胀
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.00,0:37:17.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,只是最初猛烈的爆炸的遗迹
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.32,0:37:26.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,大爆炸意味着，在过去
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.60,0:37:29.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,宇宙比它今天的样子要小很多
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.12,0:37:34.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,从那时到现在，它正在变得更大
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.56,0:37:47.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,根据大爆炸理论
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.04,0:37:52.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,宇宙在过去138亿年一直在膨胀
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.32,0:37:54.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在大多数时间里
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.12,0:37:57.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你希望这种膨胀会慢下来
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.08,0:37:59.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为宇宙中所有质量的
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.52,0:38:02.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,万有引力组合起来
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.04,0:38:04.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,会试图把物质拉回到一起
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.76,0:38:06.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,现在，这里有一个好点子
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.04,0:38:08.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,宇宙学家认识到通过测量
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.64,0:38:10.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,膨胀慢下来的速度
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.92,0:38:14.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们就能计算太空中有多少物质
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.84,0:38:18.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,从某种意义上来说，这会让他们能称量整个宇宙的重量
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.40,0:38:25.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是，为了测量宇宙是如何膨胀的
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.00,0:38:29.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你需要一种可靠的方法来测量空间的距离
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.24,0:38:41.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,对于已知亮度的东西，天文学家称其为标准蜡烛
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.40,0:38:47.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个灯笼里面的火焰产生的光量是固定的
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.08,0:38:51.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它具有特定的亮度，我可以在此地测量它
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.80,0:38:55.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是当我放开灯笼，它就会飘走
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.08,0:38:57.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,随着它飘得越来越远
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.84,0:38:59.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它的光也会显得越来越暗
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.60,0:39:04.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为我知道它真正的亮度是多少
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.92,0:39:08.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,把它显示的亮度与真正的亮度相比较
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.16,0:39:11.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我就能计算出它在多远的地方
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.00,0:39:36.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为每一个灯笼的实际亮度都是一样的
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.84,0:39:39.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我就能通过亮度来计算
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.68,0:39:42.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我在天空中看到的任何灯笼的距离
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.80,0:39:50.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,天文学中与中国灯笼等价的是
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.92,0:39:57.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一种特殊的爆发星，叫做1a型超新星
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.00,0:40:16.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这些恒星总是在它们到达相同的临界质量的时候爆炸
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.36,0:40:19.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以总是发出同样的亮度
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.88,0:40:25.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以通过测量它们看起来有多亮
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.52,0:40:28.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们就能告诉你它们离地球有多远
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.52,0:40:35.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,除了告诉我们它们有多远
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.60,0:40:40.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,从超新星到达地球的光还能告诉我们其他一些情况
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.52,0:40:44.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当光穿过宇宙时，它会伸展
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.56,0:40:48.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为光穿过的空间正在膨胀
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.40,0:40:53.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,随着它的波长的增加，光变得原来越红
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.96,0:40:59.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这种红移告诉我们在光离开它的源的时候，
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.40,0:41:03.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当新星爆炸的时候，宇宙膨胀有多快
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.64,0:41:12.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是当科学家分析从更远处传来的光的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.40,0:41:14.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们发现了奇怪的情况
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.96,0:41:17.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,光的伸展量比预期的要小
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.68,0:41:21.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这就意味着，在过去
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.80,0:41:25.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,宇宙的膨胀要比现在更慢
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.96,0:41:30.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,换句话说，宇宙的膨胀完全不是在变慢
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.96,0:41:32.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而是越来越快
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.12,0:41:41.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,能够让宇宙加速膨胀的唯一方式...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.96,0:41:48.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,..就是，是否有一种神秘的新力在把它分离
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.12,0:41:55.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就像在面对暗物质时一样，物理学家认为理解
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.88,0:41:58.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这种新的力之关键
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.12,0:42:01.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,可能隐藏于最小可能的尺度中...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.56,0:42:08.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,..因为量子物理学似乎提供了一种已有的解释
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.04,0:42:16.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,根据量子场论，真空包含万物，而不是空的
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.24,0:42:19.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,粒子不断地出现和消失
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.76,0:42:23.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,创造出从真空本身借来的能量
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.60,0:42:29.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,物理学家期望这种理论上的真空能量
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.28,0:42:33.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,可能就是推动宇宙分离的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.20,0:42:37.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个理论使我们能计算真空的
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.44,0:42:41.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,能量密度，也就是在一个给定的体积内你希望
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.08,0:42:42.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,找到的能量数量
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.96,0:42:46.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这样的话，如果我从真空获得的能量
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.84,0:42:51.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就是对j求和1/2乘h-bar乘欧米茄j
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.60,0:42:53.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,并且如果我取截断能量
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.80,0:42:56.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,为10万亿电子伏特的量级
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.72,0:42:58.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个量级恰好高于大型强子对撞机上
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.60,0:43:01.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,已知的物理学，那么真空的公式...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.88,0:43:06.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们需要做的只是核对一下理论所预测的能量密度
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.48,0:43:11.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,匹配驱动宇宙加速膨胀所需要的能量密度
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.12,0:43:14.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这样这种神秘的力就能得到解释了
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.20,0:43:20.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,『他念叨着方程』
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.64,0:43:42.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这样，就给了我一个真空的真空的能量密度值
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.56,0:43:47.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,为每立方米10的35次方千克
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.84,0:43:53.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,麻烦的是，天文学家所观测到的值
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.08,0:43:57.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是10的-27次方千克每立方米
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.48,0:44:00.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这意味着，理论上的数与实验上的数据
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.64,0:44:04.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,相差10的62次方倍
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.72,0:44:07.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也就是1的后面跟62个零
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.88,0:44:11.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,为了让你对这种错误的程度有些感觉
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.40,0:44:14.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这就相当于说，从大爆炸到现在只过了
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.56,0:44:19.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,10到17秒，整个可视宇宙的直径
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.40,0:44:22.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,只有10到27米...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.12,0:44:25.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以这是一个相当大的错误
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.48,0:44:32.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这意味着无论是什么在实际推动宇宙分离
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.72,0:44:35.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它都是某种全新的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.04,0:44:43.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,真相是，对是什么导致宇宙膨胀的加速
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.04,0:44:45.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们知道的很少很少
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.76,0:44:49.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是我们却给它取了一个名字 - 暗能量
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.52,0:44:52.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而且我们知道，为了让它能够起发挥应有的效应
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.08,0:44:54.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,周围必须存在极多的暗能量
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.32,0:45:01.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,爱因斯坦的著名公式E=mc^2
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.04,0:45:05.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,说能量与物质是同一种东西的不同形式
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.96,0:45:09.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,暗能量的等价质量使宇宙中
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.40,0:45:11.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,其他所有东西的质量相形见绌
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.72,0:45:15.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这就意味着，在今天，
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.96,0:45:19.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,正常的物质只占宇宙的4%
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.88,0:45:23.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,宇宙的23%是难以捉摸的暗物质
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.64,0:45:28.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而宇宙庞大的73%
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.68,0:45:31.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,都由神秘的暗能量组成
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.28,0:45:38.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,试想一下
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.64,0:45:40.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,1千亿个星系
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.72,0:45:44.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,每个星系包含超过1千亿的恒星
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.60,0:45:48.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这些恒星反过来又是数不清的行星和卫星的家园
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.72,0:45:55.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所有这些只是漂泊在巨大的深不可测的海洋中的废料
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.88,0:46:00.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,暗物质我们看不见，暗能量我们几乎不能理解
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.28,0:46:09.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,暗能量的本质意味着宇宙正变得
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.92,0:46:12.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,更加不可知了
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.92,0:46:19.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,随着空间的膨胀，间距变得更大
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.68,0:46:24.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,大多数作用力变得更弱了，因为你有同样的质量或电荷
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.04,0:46:27.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,只是现在每样物质都分开得更远了
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.40,0:46:32.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是暗能量的行为完全不同
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.88,0:46:37.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,随着宇宙的膨胀，它变得更强了
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.44,0:46:40.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,空间越多，暗能量就越多
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.56,0:46:43.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这样宇宙就膨胀得越快
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.88,0:46:47.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,同时就会创造更多的空间和更多的暗能量
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.20,0:46:56.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这就会有一个深远的后果
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.48,0:46:59.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就像暗物质把星系拉在一起
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.88,0:47:02.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,创造了我们已知的宇宙一样...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.56,0:47:07.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,..暗能量则会把宇宙撕开
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.64,0:47:12.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在未来，随着空间膨胀越来越大
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.04,0:47:15.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,暗能量将会变得更加站主导地位
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.32,0:47:19.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就这样，暗能量最终会塑造宇宙的命运
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.08,0:47:22.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果暗能量继续增加，就像现在这样，
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.60,0:47:26.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那么，它就会把星系推得越来越远
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.16,0:47:29.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,直到，最终，它们离开我们的视野
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.36,0:47:33.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这样的宇宙将会变得更加黑暗
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.40,0:47:34.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也更加孤寂
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.04,0:47:49.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,现代宇宙学的终极目标
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.24,0:47:52.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就是理解暗能量和宇宙的命运，
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.68,0:47:56.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,并见证暗物质最初是如何
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.72,0:47:58.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,把万物聚集在一起的
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.60,0:48:08.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以，为了完全理解宇宙的开始和结局
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.40,0:48:13.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,宇宙学家们开始着手构建宏伟巨作 -
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.08,0:48:18.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,把宇宙的整个生命周期中空间的每一处都绘制出来...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.72,0:48:24.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,..从宇宙过去的最黑暗时期开始，
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.68,0:48:29.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那是大爆炸消褪的晚霞余辉出现的年代
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.16,0:48:34.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们谈论起宇宙的寿命，就像
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.32,0:48:38.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在谈论我们自己的生命各阶段一样，从它的诞生，
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.24,0:48:42.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,经过童年，青春期，成年直到死亡.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.52,0:48:45.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以绘制宇宙图像实际上就是
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.36,0:48:48.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,填补宇宙生命的相册
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.32,0:48:54.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这里是我的一张相片，那是20年前和我的孩子们在一起.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.96,0:48:57.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我知道那是啥时候，因为我那时头发更多.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.56,0:49:01.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而这张我的照片是在我20多年前大学毕业的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.76,0:49:03.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这张里面的我还是一个青少年
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.80,0:49:08.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,用同样的方式，通过观察太空
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.92,0:49:10.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们有很好的宇宙图像
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.92,0:49:13.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,直到宇宙的青少年时期
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.12,0:49:16.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那时候星系刚开始形成
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.72,0:49:21.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但在此之前的，我们只有唯一一张图片
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.04,0:49:24.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是宇宙只有40万年的时候的图片
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.96,0:49:29.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就是宇宙微波背景 - 那就是大爆炸的晚霞余晖
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.56,0:49:32.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这就好像是，在我一生的相册中,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.56,0:49:36.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这张我16岁时候的照片，再往前就啥都没有了
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.20,0:49:39.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,除了这张我和我父母在伊拉克的照片，
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.52,0:49:41.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那时候我只有几个月大
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.32,0:49:46.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这种宇宙童年时期的空白
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.20,0:49:50.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也就是从宇宙最早时期，到第一批
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.08,0:49:54.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,恒星的诞生，形成大星系
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.12,0:49:57.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这段时期就是宇宙的黑暗时代
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.28,0:50:08.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,宇宙的黑暗时代持续了大约十亿年
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.64,0:50:12.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,得到这样的名称，是因为那个年代只有极珍贵的很少的
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.12,0:50:13.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,恒星点缀着宇宙
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.52,0:50:23.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以，为了填补宇宙相册的那些空白页面，我们需要
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.28,0:50:27.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一种东西能够看到几乎没有光的地方
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.32,0:50:38.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在二次大战时期，伯纳德·洛弗尔开发了一种设备
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.80,0:50:41.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,能够看透黑暗
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.08,0:50:43.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他曾经从事机载雷达的工作
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.00,0:50:45.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,为轰炸机绘制地面目标
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.20,0:50:51.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是他真正的雄心在于建造
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.28,0:50:54.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,某种能描绘天国的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.76,0:51:30.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,卓瑞尔河岸的巨型碟盘就是伯纳德·洛弗尔的杰作
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.52,0:51:34.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在设计它的时候，它是世界上最大的全机动的
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.92,0:51:38.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,射电望远镜，能够搜索整个天空
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.16,0:51:41.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,能够检测到来自太空最深处的
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.52,0:51:44.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,最长波长的辐射信号
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.12,0:52:09.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,洛弗尔望远镜的接收面积
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.60,0:52:13.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,为4560平方米，
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.56,0:52:19.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,用了超过2400块的镀锌钢板
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.28,0:52:28.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在原来的设计中，望远镜的这个大碗
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.08,0:52:30.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,并不像这样固化
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.72,0:52:34.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,原来的规划是用轻得多的金属丝网
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.80,0:52:39.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,后来人们重新设计了这个盘子
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.76,0:52:44.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为天文学家们发现了一种看透黑暗的新方法
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.36,0:52:47.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这种方法可能最终能让他们
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.32,0:52:50.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,绘制宇宙的黑暗时代
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.44,0:52:55.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,氢原子弥漫着每一个星系
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.80,0:52:57.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它是在大爆炸中产生的
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.28,0:53:01.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是所有常规物质,包括我们身体的基本成分.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.08,0:53:03.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就像所有常规物质一样
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.36,0:53:06.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,氢原子只会发出特定的光
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.48,0:53:09.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是后来天文学家发现了某种不同寻常的现象
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.84,0:53:11.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当氢原子在太空漂浮的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.88,0:53:16.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,中性的氢原子气体总是持续产生无线电波
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.36,0:53:22.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而且最关键的是，这些波的波长总是一样的 - 21厘米
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.84,0:53:26.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这就意味着对于充满了氢原子的星系
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.52,0:53:28.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,氢原子能够将它们描绘出来
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.84,0:53:36.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,通过探测21厘米信号，洛弗尔望远镜帮助揭示了
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.08,0:53:39.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,银河系的螺旋结构
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.84,0:53:43.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,并绘制了远距离星系的细节图像
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.04,0:53:52.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是星系并不是宇宙中含有氢气的唯一地方
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.20,0:53:54.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在宇宙的黑暗时代
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.12,0:53:58.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,没有星系，却又足量的氢气
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.08,0:54:03.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以，通过探测这些原生气体云发出的21厘米信号
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.08,0:54:05.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你就能看到婴儿期的宇宙
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.68,0:54:08.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,从而窥视到黑暗时代本身
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.12,0:54:18.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,通过这种方式，我们将能够看到暗物质
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.96,0:54:20.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,把宇宙拉在一起...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.80,0:54:24.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,..并点亮天国
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.12,0:54:31.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就是在黑暗时代，在大爆炸中产生的氢气
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.32,0:54:36.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,被压缩成恒星，再构成星系
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.36,0:54:41.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就是在这个年代，我们所知道的宇宙诞生了
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.12,0:54:44.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,并被暗物质的引力所雕塑
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.20,0:54:55.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,科学家们正在建造新设备来绘制黑暗时代
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.00,0:54:57.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它将比目前看到的多很多
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.64,0:55:03.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它的有效接收面积比洛弗尔望远镜
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.24,0:55:07.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,大200倍，平方千米阵列
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.16,0:55:10.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,将能够描绘十亿个星系
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.76,0:55:15.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,跟踪整个宇宙的膨胀和演化
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.08,0:55:17.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,并且比以前更精确
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.96,0:55:25.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们期望，通过这种方法
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.36,0:55:29.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它能够提供一些关于暗能量性质的线索
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.00,0:55:31.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,以及宇宙终极命运的线索
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.40,0:55:56.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,用氢原子描绘宇宙可能只代表
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.48,0:56:02.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,人类用光探索宇宙的最后篇章
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.08,0:56:07.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个探索的旅程开始于大约400年前
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.28,0:56:12.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在1609年十二月，伽利略·伽利莱开始
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.28,0:56:14.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,观察黑夜的天空
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.28,0:56:17.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在那之前，外太空存在什么
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.40,0:56:19.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,只是一个信仰问题
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.20,0:56:23.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,整个宇宙，看不见的和不能看见的，就在那里
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.00,0:56:24.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是现在，第一次
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.72,0:56:27.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,天国的本性成为可知的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.88,0:56:31.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你只需要抬头仰望就行
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.04,0:56:34.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,进入到伽利略简陋的望远镜中的光线
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.24,0:56:37.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,开启了一系列的发现，揭示了
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.56,0:56:39.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,宇宙的真实本性
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.24,0:56:49.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们已经看到的星系
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.48,0:56:52.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,远离地球数十亿光年
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.00,0:56:58.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当我们理解了光的属性
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.36,0:57:01.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们又发现了组成恒星的物质...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.28,0:57:08.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,..并瞥见了宇宙自己的起点
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.80,0:57:21.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是人们认识到，许多常规物质我们看不到
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.60,0:57:26.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,还有暗物质和暗能量的发现
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.64,0:57:32.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,意味着宇宙的99%都隐藏于阴影之中
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.40,0:57:40.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,随着暗能量把星系分离得更远
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.32,0:57:43.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那里少量的光源将开始离我们远去
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.40,0:57:48.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,随着宇宙更快地膨胀
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.24,0:57:52.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一个一个的星系将从我们的视野消失
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.72,0:57:57.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,仍然能够看见的将只有我们自己星系中的恒星
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.12,0:58:00.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那就像我们从来没有发明过望远镜的时候一样
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.84,0:58:04.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,对于绝大多数宇宙中的生命来说
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.64,0:58:08.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们将无法做出和我们一样的关于宇宙的发现
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.12,0:58:14.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以，尽管宇宙中如此多的东西隐藏于阴影之中
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.16,0:58:16.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但我不会感到沮丧
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.40,0:58:17.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,真实的奇迹就是
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.56,0:58:20.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当我们第一次向太空深处望去时
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.80,0:58:23.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,居然还能看到有光
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.84,0:58:36.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,无论你想走进光明
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.44,0:58:38.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,还是想探索黑暗的神秘
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.96,0:58:41.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,让开放大学来激励你
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.52,0:58:42.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,请到
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.40,0:58:48.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,..顺着这个链接到开放大学
